00:03:44,541 --> 00:03:49,041
Good morning, papa.
- Good morning, son.

5
00:03:49,042 --> 00:03:52,333
Hey, get up. You've to go to
school. - Has he not got up till yet?

6
00:03:52,416 --> 00:03:53,999
Hey, Raj, get up. See,
grandma has come now.

7
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:55,166
The father doesn't have a night...

8
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:56,749
...and the son doesn't
have a morning.

9
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:59,582
Come on, have your milk.
And you tell me...

10
00:03:59,583 --> 00:04:01,374
You have been sleeping
half and incomplete...

11
00:04:01,375 --> 00:04:03,707
...since so many months, how many
more nights will you stay awake?

12
00:04:03,708 --> 00:04:05,916
Mother, last night was the last
time that I would stay awake.

13
00:04:05,917 --> 00:04:08,749
The project on which I
was working is over.

14
00:04:08,750 --> 00:04:13,750
Come, I will show you. Come on, son.

15
00:04:17,917 --> 00:04:21,415
Papa, you have made a wonderful car.

16
00:04:21,416 --> 00:04:22,916
Did you like it, mother?

17
00:04:22,917 --> 00:04:26,291
It is very good son. But you have
worked on it too, isn't it?

18
00:04:26,750 --> 00:04:28,415
Some companies have offered me.

19
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:31,625
After applying for the patent, I
have to hold meetings with them.

20
00:04:41,416 --> 00:04:44,458
I am Mr. Rakesh Kapoor.
- Hi. - And these are my partners.

21
00:04:57,708 --> 00:05:02,375
Please come.

22
00:05:13,375 --> 00:05:18,833
This is an eight-cylinder V-engine.

23
00:05:28,500 --> 00:05:30,415
And all this technology
is controlled...

24
00:05:30,416 --> 00:05:33,415
...by computer diagnosis systems.

25
00:05:33,416 --> 00:05:39,125
If the car meets with
an accident, that is.

26
00:05:47,500 --> 00:05:50,415
In making this car, I have paid...

27
00:05:50,416 --> 00:05:51,999
...most of my attention
to the high seating...

28
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:57,292
...and excellent road
hold to the driver.

29
00:05:59,708 --> 00:06:03,374
You have made such
a beautiful design.

30
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:05,791
We like your project a lot.

31
00:06:05,792 --> 00:06:07,958
Tell me. What kind of deal
would you wish to make?

32
00:06:07,959 --> 00:06:09,916
I want twenty percent
of the royalty.

33
00:06:09,917 --> 00:06:14,374
The car's logo will be of my name.

34
00:06:14,375 --> 00:06:16,541
We are very impressed
by your design.

35
00:06:16,542 --> 00:06:20,374
But... But we can't understand
these terms of yours.

36
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:23,374
Sir, my terms are because of
the beauties of my project.

37
00:06:23,375 --> 00:06:26,374
My car is a futuristic car.

38
00:06:26,375 --> 00:06:28,374
And as you people must have seen...

39
00:06:28,375 --> 00:06:29,874
...there isn't any car
made like this...

40
00:06:29,875 --> 00:06:31,916
...which has so many features in it.

41
00:06:31,917 --> 00:06:33,541
And having such good
fuel efficiency too.

42
00:06:33,542 --> 00:06:35,999
We agree that you have made
a excellent car model.

43
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,749
But we have to keep our company...

44
00:06:37,750 --> 00:06:39,833
...name's value in the market.

45
00:06:39,834 --> 00:06:42,582
Therefore, we cannot give your name.

46
00:06:42,583 --> 00:06:45,708
But we will pay whatever you
wish for this project.

47
00:06:45,917 --> 00:06:49,042
But we cannot give you
royalty or partnership.

48
00:06:51,667 --> 00:06:57,125
I do not agree to your deal.

49
00:07:01,333 --> 00:07:06,791
Give him back his disc.

50
00:07:11,375 --> 00:07:14,041
You have made a very
advanced machine.

51
00:07:14,042 --> 00:07:16,374
I don't think that such
a machine can be made...

52
00:07:16,375 --> 00:07:18,791
...in the automobile industry
in the next ten years.

53
00:07:18,792 --> 00:07:21,374
We accept all your conditions.

54
00:07:21,375 --> 00:07:24,374
We will give you a royalty, and
give the car your name too.

55
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:26,916
I have a discussion with my
technical team tomorrow.

56
00:07:26,917 --> 00:07:28,874
After that, the next week...

57
00:07:28,875 --> 00:07:34,083
We will sign the agreement.

58
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:39,417
Mother...

59
00:07:39,917 --> 00:07:41,499
Hey, have you come?

60
00:07:41,500 --> 00:07:44,875
My project deal is finalized. I am
signing the contract next week.

61
00:07:44,959 --> 00:07:51,459
I knew it. True hard work
is never a waste.

62
00:07:54,417 --> 00:07:57,542
Even I have made a car.
- Is it?

63
00:08:00,750 --> 00:08:02,833
You will become a greater
engineer than me.

64
00:08:02,834 --> 00:08:05,833
This can't be possible.
- Why?

65
00:08:05,834 --> 00:08:09,332
Because I can't keep awake
at nights like you.

66
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:14,042
Donkey!

67
00:08:21,458 --> 00:08:23,708
Papa, why do you wash it everyday?

68
00:08:23,709 --> 00:08:26,708
I make you bathe everyday too,
isn't it? - But why?

69
00:08:26,709 --> 00:08:28,541
The thing that we love...

70
00:08:28,542 --> 00:08:30,874
...shouldn't we keep
his lovely always?

71
00:08:30,875 --> 00:08:33,916
Do you love this car very much?
- Yes.

72
00:08:33,917 --> 00:08:36,374
Why? Papa?

73
00:08:36,375 --> 00:08:39,792
Son, this is my father's symbol.
He had gifted it to me.

74
00:08:40,041 --> 00:08:46,500
I will gift it to you
when you grow up.

75
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:51,582
Papa, why have you put this Tarzan?

76
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:53,499
I had kept it here in my childhood.

77
00:08:53,500 --> 00:08:55,457
I believed this car
to be Tarzan and...

78
00:08:55,458 --> 00:08:57,416
...I had even named it as Tarzan.

79
00:08:57,417 --> 00:08:58,958
Tarzan was a man.

80
00:08:58,959 --> 00:09:02,292
Yes, he was a man. But was
strong like this machine.

81
00:09:02,417 --> 00:09:04,999
But papa, Tarzan used
to eat food too.

82
00:09:05,000 --> 00:09:06,666
Where does this car eat food?

83
00:09:06,667 --> 00:09:09,916
Doesn't it?

84
00:09:09,917 --> 00:09:13,332
Then why doesn't it wear clothes?

85
00:09:13,333 --> 00:09:15,666
Even Tarzan didn't wear any clothes.

86
00:09:15,667 --> 00:09:17,332
Just because the censor shouldn't...

87
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:18,916
...object, the movie
and cartoon Tarzan...

88
00:09:18,917 --> 00:09:20,957
...were made to wear a knickers
made of leaves. - But.

89
00:09:20,958 --> 00:09:23,624
Now don't ask me what a censor is.

90
00:09:23,625 --> 00:09:29,791
It is your phone, son.
- I am coming, mother.

91
00:09:29,792 --> 00:09:31,874
I am Mukund Joshi speaking
from Harsh Motors.

92
00:09:31,875 --> 00:09:34,374
Yes, Mr. Joshi...

93
00:09:34,375 --> 00:09:38,417
Our company doesn't wish
to deal with you. - Why?

94
00:09:38,542 --> 00:09:40,582
The design which you say is yours...

95
00:09:40,583 --> 00:09:42,708
...and using which you wish
to deal with the company...

96
00:09:42,709 --> 00:09:46,417
...Four Fox company has patented
it three months ago.

97
00:09:48,834 --> 00:09:50,915
But... I have completed
the design four...

98
00:09:50,916 --> 00:09:52,749
...days ago and patented
it. Then how...

99
00:09:52,750 --> 00:09:54,457
...come Four Fox patent
it three months ago?

100
00:09:54,458 --> 00:10:00,084
We don't know that. You ask them.

101
00:10:03,417 --> 00:10:05,833
I have an idea.
- What?

102
00:10:05,834 --> 00:10:07,915
We won't make this car ourselves.

103
00:10:07,916 --> 00:10:09,915
Instead, we will give
this car's design...

104
00:10:09,916 --> 00:10:11,416
...to some German or Japanese...

105
00:10:11,417 --> 00:10:14,666
...company and eat it's royalty
throughout life. - Yes!

106
00:10:14,667 --> 00:10:18,792
We cannot give royalty, but we can
take it, isn't it? - Surely.

107
00:10:19,417 --> 00:10:22,958
A stolen thing shouldn't be
dangled by the neck as it is.

108
00:10:23,417 --> 00:10:26,458
Because the one who owns the
thing will strangle you.

109
00:10:27,417 --> 00:10:29,583
You patented my design in your...

110
00:10:29,584 --> 00:10:32,709
...name by bribing the
patent registrar.

111
00:10:32,875 --> 00:10:34,874
We did that, all right.

112
00:10:34,875 --> 00:10:38,416
And you cannot harm
us in anyway now.

113
00:10:38,417 --> 00:10:41,416
I have the receipt of
the patent application.

114
00:10:41,417 --> 00:10:43,583
I will take you four foxes and the...

115
00:10:43,584 --> 00:10:46,416
...patent registrar to the court.

116
00:10:46,417 --> 00:10:50,333
I still have so much proof that
I can have you four arrested.

117
00:10:51,417 --> 00:10:57,209
I will go to the police station
right away and expose you.

118
00:11:04,667 --> 00:11:06,915
I have got the information.
They are not in the office.

119
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,666
They have gone to the farmhouse.

120
00:11:08,667 --> 00:11:11,416
Have you brought your
proofs with you?

121
00:11:11,417 --> 00:11:12,957
The CD of my designs and the...

122
00:11:12,958 --> 00:11:15,832
...receipt of the patent
application is with me.

123
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:18,958
We will go to their farmhouse
right away. - Come on.

124
00:11:28,750 --> 00:11:33,416
But listen to me carefully. The
agreement that we signed...

125
00:11:33,417 --> 00:11:35,708
He has registered a complaint.

126
00:11:35,709 --> 00:11:38,416
You people have stolen
the designs of his car.

127
00:11:38,417 --> 00:11:41,499
And at this time, he has
the proof with him too.

128
00:11:41,500 --> 00:11:44,416
He had come to us to sell his car.

129
00:11:44,417 --> 00:11:47,709
We didn't complete the deal
so we copied his CD.

130
00:11:47,875 --> 00:11:50,749
We also knew that if he
goes to the court...

131
00:11:50,750 --> 00:11:53,583
...we will have to fight
the case for many years.

132
00:11:53,584 --> 00:11:55,874
And we won't have anything
in our hands.

133
00:11:55,875 --> 00:11:58,416
You are right.

134
00:11:58,417 --> 00:12:00,749
Please give them all the proof.

135
00:12:00,750 --> 00:12:04,416
The problem will be solved.

136
00:12:04,417 --> 00:12:06,832
Hey, there isn't any
need to be shocked.

137
00:12:06,833 --> 00:12:09,666
We own that inspector.

138
00:12:09,667 --> 00:12:13,416
It was your bad luck
that you went to him.

139
00:12:13,417 --> 00:12:16,625
And we know that you wouldn't
give us the proof.

140
00:12:16,750 --> 00:12:19,082
Therefore, he will kill you now.

141
00:12:19,083 --> 00:12:24,291
And he will close your file too.

142
00:12:24,417 --> 00:12:27,832
I had heard that every
dog has it's day.

143
00:12:27,833 --> 00:12:32,416
But I hadn't heard any
phrase for foxes.

144
00:12:32,417 --> 00:12:35,459
You committed a huge mistake
my calling me here.

145
00:12:36,417 --> 00:12:38,583
I am an automobile engineer.

146
00:12:38,584 --> 00:12:43,625
I can ruin the design
as well as make it!

147
00:13:37,750 --> 00:13:43,458
He broke my leg! That dog!

148
00:13:51,417 --> 00:13:53,915
I will call the police
and press now.

149
00:13:53,916 --> 00:13:57,500
I will strip your uniform with
the skin of these four people.

150
00:14:10,375 --> 00:14:16,166
What do you think? Are there
saints and seers in business?

151
00:14:20,916 --> 00:14:23,665
You will ruin the design? Take this!

152
00:14:23,666 --> 00:14:27,416
You call us foxes?

153
00:14:27,417 --> 00:14:28,749
Please stop.

154
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:30,499
Don't kill him here.

155
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:33,583
We will put him in his car and
put him in the lake behind.

156
00:14:33,584 --> 00:14:36,625
It will never be found out whether
it was an accident or a murder.

157
00:14:36,750 --> 00:14:42,542
The inspector is right.
- Okay.

158
00:15:16,375 --> 00:15:20,417
We will give you name and royalty
both in your rebirth.

159
00:15:48,417 --> 00:15:50,416
Go. Go and design a flying machine...

160
00:15:50,417 --> 00:15:55,959
...for the God of Death, Go!

161
00:16:31,417 --> 00:16:35,833
Hey, battery! Don't you see
even after wearing glasses?

162
00:16:36,083 --> 00:16:37,916
That place is not for
parking your cycle.

163
00:16:37,917 --> 00:16:39,582
It is for parking our bikes.

164
00:16:39,583 --> 00:16:40,790
So where should I park?

165
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:42,916
Hey, do you think that we
are parking instructors?

166
00:16:42,917 --> 00:16:47,959
Come on, park it anywhere.

167
00:16:50,417 --> 00:16:55,916
Hey, battery. Come here. Come here.

168
00:16:55,917 --> 00:16:59,541
See, battery. You passed
and came into our class.

169
00:16:59,666 --> 00:17:00,916
What does that mean?

170
00:17:00,917 --> 00:17:03,832
This means that you
failed this time too?

171
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:06,624
Are you very happy?
- No. I am sorry.

172
00:17:06,625 --> 00:17:09,708
You are expressing your sorrow with
such happiness. - Come here.

173
00:17:10,375 --> 00:17:12,790
Come here.

174
00:17:12,791 --> 00:17:16,750
Okay, tell me. How is two and two?
- Yes?

175
00:17:16,875 --> 00:17:19,749
What are you stammering for?
Tell me how much they are?

176
00:17:19,750 --> 00:17:20,957
Two and two are four.

177
00:17:20,958 --> 00:17:24,374
You fool. Two and two
are twenty-two, what?

178
00:17:24,375 --> 00:17:27,457
Tell me, how much is it?

179
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:29,624
Twenty-two.

180
00:17:29,625 --> 00:17:32,832
Now he has come in our category.

181
00:17:32,833 --> 00:17:35,540
What is going on?
- Oh God! Double battery!

182
00:17:35,541 --> 00:17:38,416
What are you doing here?
- Nothing sir.

183
00:17:38,417 --> 00:17:40,832
Everyone calls this
poor kid as battery.

184
00:17:40,833 --> 00:17:43,582
We were just asking
him his real name.

185
00:17:43,583 --> 00:17:47,958
No sir. No body else, they
call me battery. - Why?

186
00:17:48,417 --> 00:17:50,416
Because I wear spectacles, isn't it?

187
00:17:50,417 --> 00:17:52,916
This means that you must be calling
me a battery too? - No sir.

188
00:17:52,917 --> 00:17:55,499
These people call you
a double battery. - What!

189
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:58,708
I will rusticate you people,
what do you think?

190
00:17:58,792 --> 00:18:00,665
You will sit here all
through your life?

191
00:18:00,666 --> 00:18:02,916
You will ruin his life too?
I won't let this happen!

192
00:18:02,917 --> 00:18:04,333
Battery, go from here!

193
00:18:04,334 --> 00:18:05,791
Raj, you go.

194
00:18:05,792 --> 00:18:08,333
You call me a double battery? Yes?

195
00:18:08,334 --> 00:18:11,750
Raj, why are you late?
- I met those four headaches.

196
00:18:12,334 --> 00:18:14,374
It seems that those
four heachaches...

197
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:16,457
...think you to be a Baburao.
- Baburao?

198
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:17,749
What is this now?

199
00:18:17,750 --> 00:18:20,415
I haven't been able to tackle
battery till now...

200
00:18:20,416 --> 00:18:22,457
...and you are giving
me another surname?

201
00:18:22,458 --> 00:18:28,292
Did you bring my books?
- I have brought them. Take these.

202
00:19:03,666 --> 00:19:08,749
It is such an item!

203
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:14,250
What a figure!

204
00:19:18,334 --> 00:19:23,792
It seems she is coming towards us.

205
00:19:26,375 --> 00:19:30,707
Can you tell me where the
principal's office is?

206
00:19:30,708 --> 00:19:34,457
In which college were
you before this?

207
00:19:34,458 --> 00:19:37,374
By the way, I asked about
the principal's office.

208
00:19:37,375 --> 00:19:41,250
Go straight and inside. There
will be stairs there.

209
00:19:41,375 --> 00:19:43,374
Go upstairs and left.
There will be...

210
00:19:43,375 --> 00:19:48,750
...the principal's office
a little farther.

211
00:20:13,416 --> 00:20:15,666
Please go!

212
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:19,415
I will come in too!

213
00:20:19,416 --> 00:20:23,958
She is angry.

214
00:20:25,416 --> 00:20:29,333
See. These are not good boys.
I will show you the...

215
00:20:29,416 --> 00:20:32,083
...principal's office.
I am not like those.

216
00:20:32,084 --> 00:20:35,707
Please come.

217
00:20:35,708 --> 00:20:40,167
Move!

218
00:20:42,416 --> 00:20:47,833
This is our principal.

219
00:20:57,416 --> 00:20:59,916
Hey, Raj, what are you doing?

220
00:20:59,917 --> 00:21:02,916
Look at this design. This
car will become like this.

221
00:21:02,917 --> 00:21:04,832
This car will become like this?

222
00:21:04,833 --> 00:21:06,916
Wow! You have made such a design.

223
00:21:06,917 --> 00:21:08,832
It's good.

224
00:21:08,833 --> 00:21:11,749
Yes. Sir is calling you.
Go and get you salary.

225
00:21:11,750 --> 00:21:14,499
Fifteen... sixteen... seventeen...
eighteen...

226
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,792
This is your salary. - Yes. -

227
00:21:17,917 --> 00:21:19,041
Sign here.

228
00:21:19,042 --> 00:21:24,666
Papa, should I lift it?
- No. Manglu, lift the phone. - Yes.

229
00:21:24,667 --> 00:21:26,083
Yes?
- This is your salary.

230
00:21:26,084 --> 00:21:30,415
I have cut the money for
three days. - Why?

231
00:21:30,416 --> 00:21:33,415
You were absent for three
weeks last month.

232
00:21:33,416 --> 00:21:34,582
Don't you remember?

233
00:21:34,583 --> 00:21:37,499
Yes... But I had to go
out with grandma.

234
00:21:37,500 --> 00:21:38,999
You tell me something.

235
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:42,707
Are you paid for my service
or grandma's service?

236
00:21:42,708 --> 00:21:46,667
Why are you staring at me
now? Go away. - Okay.

237
00:21:50,416 --> 00:21:51,582
Yes, papa?

238
00:21:51,583 --> 00:21:53,415
I had kept the curd milk in
the jug with ice to cool off.

239
00:21:53,416 --> 00:21:54,749
Where has it gone?

240
00:21:54,750 --> 00:21:57,415
There was a client here.
His car was hot.

241
00:21:57,416 --> 00:21:59,415
I put it in his radiator
for coolness.

242
00:21:59,416 --> 00:22:01,541
You put my curd milk
in his radiator?

243
00:22:01,542 --> 00:22:02,874
There was nothing more cold.

244
00:22:02,875 --> 00:22:04,041
So you should have
put my head in it.

245
00:22:04,042 --> 00:22:05,749
I would have done that.
But your head is hot!

246
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:08,749
What if the radiator caught fire?

247
00:22:08,750 --> 00:22:10,999
Explain this son of
a fool something!

248
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,291
Otherwise he will stay like a
used the outside the garage.

249
00:22:14,416 --> 00:22:19,000
The fool!

250
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:33,375
Grandma!

251
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:36,415
Tell me. How was your
first day in college?

252
00:22:36,416 --> 00:22:37,999
Grandma, is the first
day of college...

253
00:22:38,000 --> 00:22:39,749
...and the last day of
school every good?

254
00:22:39,750 --> 00:22:42,415
Yes, but seventy five percent
of my day was very good.

255
00:22:42,416 --> 00:22:45,415
Why was the rest twenty
five percent bad?

256
00:22:45,416 --> 00:22:51,208
Some of my seniors asked some
stupid questions to me.

257
00:22:52,708 --> 00:22:54,833
Grandma, can I ask you something?

258
00:22:54,834 --> 00:22:57,749
How do I look like?

259
00:22:57,750 --> 00:23:00,041
I mean... do I look good?

260
00:23:00,042 --> 00:23:02,707
Son, you are one in a million.

261
00:23:02,708 --> 00:23:04,374
Please don't joke, grandma.

262
00:23:04,375 --> 00:23:07,374
Think that you weren't
seventy but eighteen.

263
00:23:07,375 --> 00:23:09,958
How would I look then?

264
00:23:09,959 --> 00:23:13,416
Why are you talking about beauty
and complexion today?

265
00:23:13,583 --> 00:23:16,749
Did you see some girl in college?
- How did you know that?

266
00:23:16,750 --> 00:23:18,749
The boys of today are very smart.

267
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,415
They know that the girls of today...

268
00:23:20,416 --> 00:23:22,833
...don't see their future
but their feature.

269
00:23:22,834 --> 00:23:24,415
Who is that girl?

270
00:23:24,416 --> 00:23:26,749
A girl has taken admission
in our college from London.

271
00:23:26,750 --> 00:23:28,749
Quite some boys are waiting
to be friends with her.

272
00:23:28,750 --> 00:23:31,582
Some of them troubled her
too. But I helped her.

273
00:23:31,583 --> 00:23:33,415
I sent her to the
principal's office.

274
00:23:33,416 --> 00:23:37,625
I understood what was seventy
percent nice in this day.

275
00:23:37,750 --> 00:23:39,666
You like this girl, isn't it?

276
00:23:39,667 --> 00:23:41,582
No, it's isn't like that.

277
00:23:41,583 --> 00:23:44,707
See, I am not your mother,
I am your grandma.

278
00:23:44,708 --> 00:23:48,291
And if I was eighteen year
old I would wish you...

279
00:23:48,417 --> 00:23:54,000
...you to approach me and talk to me.

280
00:24:38,417 --> 00:24:43,958
What are you staring at?

281
00:24:46,417 --> 00:24:47,582
For what?

282
00:24:47,583 --> 00:24:48,958
You left me to the principal's
office yesterday.

283
00:24:48,959 --> 00:24:54,125
And I didn't even thank you.

284
00:24:57,417 --> 00:24:59,582
Okay, I have to prepare some notes.

285
00:24:59,583 --> 00:25:04,917
Even I have to prepare some notes.

286
00:25:06,375 --> 00:25:11,083
Look at that.

287
00:25:23,375 --> 00:25:26,792
How fortunate the library is...!

288
00:25:26,917 --> 00:25:30,417
No, that rubber of the pencil.

289
00:25:32,417 --> 00:25:36,416
If only, I would be that rubber.

290
00:25:36,417 --> 00:25:40,458
All of you wait here and
see what Rocky does.

291
00:25:45,417 --> 00:25:48,416
I have been searching you to
say sorry since yesterday.

292
00:25:48,417 --> 00:25:51,416
The path to the principal's
office that I showed you...

293
00:25:51,417 --> 00:25:52,957
...I told you right turn instead
of left turn by mistake...

294
00:25:52,958 --> 00:25:55,666
...and you reached the gent's toilet.

295
00:25:55,667 --> 00:25:59,000
As it is, some mischief is
tolerated in friendship, isn't it?

296
00:26:01,625 --> 00:26:03,040
If you do any mischief
with me the next time...

297
00:26:03,041 --> 00:26:04,708
...I won't complain
to the principal...

298
00:26:04,709 --> 00:26:09,375
...but to the commissioner directly.

299
00:26:19,458 --> 00:26:21,915
Even a professor must not have
scolded Rocky like this.

300
00:26:21,916 --> 00:26:24,541
But you seemed more
scared than Rocky.

301
00:26:24,542 --> 00:26:26,541
No, why will I be scared?
- Okay listen.

302
00:26:26,542 --> 00:26:28,374
Our college came is going next week.

303
00:26:28,375 --> 00:26:30,416
I have put your name in it too.
And you too are coming.

304
00:26:30,417 --> 00:26:32,416
No friend. I can't come.
- Why?

305
00:26:32,417 --> 00:26:34,541
There is a lot of work in the
garage. And uncle will shout!

306
00:26:34,542 --> 00:26:36,833
Hey, your uncle always shouts.

307
00:26:36,834 --> 00:26:40,292
Let him shout. My household
works because of him.

308
00:26:41,667 --> 00:26:46,209
Okay, friend.

309
00:26:53,834 --> 00:26:58,458
Your purse...

310
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:45,832
You here?

311
00:27:45,833 --> 00:27:49,416
Your purse, it had fallen
down in the college.

312
00:27:49,417 --> 00:27:52,416
But you could give this purse
to me tomorrow too. - I could.

313
00:27:52,417 --> 00:27:54,749
But this purse had some your keys,
money and credit cards.

314
00:27:54,750 --> 00:27:56,749
And it even had your
driving license.

315
00:27:56,750 --> 00:27:58,791
I thought whether you would
be worried the whole night.

316
00:27:58,792 --> 00:28:01,499
You took such a huge
risk for my worry?

317
00:28:01,500 --> 00:28:04,332
What would something
have happened to you?

318
00:28:04,333 --> 00:28:05,915
You have come to my house
for the first time.

319
00:28:05,916 --> 00:28:09,874
You will have to drink tea.

320
00:28:09,875 --> 00:28:11,749
What happened?
- Sometime else.

321
00:28:11,750 --> 00:28:14,541
That means I will have to drop the
purse again, isn't it? - No!

322
00:28:14,542 --> 00:28:19,209
I will surely come.

323
00:28:24,375 --> 00:28:26,374
Are you hurt?
- No!

324
00:28:26,375 --> 00:28:32,250
I will come to have some tea.
- Surely.

325
00:29:38,459 --> 00:29:40,957
Why have you put this Tarzan?

326
00:29:40,958 --> 00:29:42,708
I had put it in my childhood.

327
00:29:42,709 --> 00:29:44,541
I thought that this car was Tarzan...

328
00:29:44,542 --> 00:29:46,374
...and I had named it Tarzan too.

329
00:29:46,375 --> 00:29:48,374
Tarzan was a man.

330
00:29:48,375 --> 00:29:51,791
Yes, he was a man. But he had
a power like this machine.

331
00:30:08,667 --> 00:30:09,790
Hey, boy!

332
00:30:09,791 --> 00:30:14,541
What are you doing here?
What do you want?

333
00:30:14,542 --> 00:30:16,790
Uncle, where did you
get this car from?

334
00:30:16,791 --> 00:30:18,999
This is not a car. This is a wreck.

335
00:30:19,000 --> 00:30:20,583
Anyone brings it from anywhere...

336
00:30:20,584 --> 00:30:22,416
...and sells it according
to it's weight.

337
00:30:22,417 --> 00:30:24,541
I want to buy it. How
much will it cost?

338
00:30:24,542 --> 00:30:26,583
It must be a wreck worth
five thousand.

339
00:30:26,584 --> 00:30:28,707
Five thousand?

340
00:30:28,708 --> 00:30:32,500
I will give you five thousand.
But I don't have it right now.

341
00:30:32,584 --> 00:30:34,416
I will take it after a week.

342
00:30:34,417 --> 00:30:36,416
All this won't do. Talk
if you have cash.

343
00:30:36,417 --> 00:30:37,832
It has half rotted already.

344
00:30:37,833 --> 00:30:39,915
Uncle, the haste that
you have to sell it...

345
00:30:39,916 --> 00:30:42,041
...I have a bigger haste to buy it.

346
00:30:42,042 --> 00:30:45,708
This car belongs to my papa.
Just a week uncle, please?

347
00:30:47,958 --> 00:30:52,874
Okay. But I won't keep
it for more than a week.

348
00:30:52,875 --> 00:30:58,208
Thank me after a week.

349
00:31:02,500 --> 00:31:06,500
Grandma...
- Yes? - Grandma! - Yes!

350
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:10,416
Hey, what is the matter?

351
00:31:10,417 --> 00:31:12,458
You seem happier than seventy
five percent today.

352
00:31:12,459 --> 00:31:14,790
My happiness doesn't have
any percentage today.

353
00:31:14,791 --> 00:31:17,458
What is such that you got?
- Sit down at least.

354
00:31:17,459 --> 00:31:19,416
What is the matter?

355
00:31:19,417 --> 00:31:22,416
Grandma, you loved papa
a lot, isn't it?

356
00:31:22,417 --> 00:31:26,292
You are asking a mother how
much she loves her son?

357
00:31:26,417 --> 00:31:29,541
So you must be loving every
thing that papa had?

358
00:31:29,542 --> 00:31:31,541
You ask this of yourself.

359
00:31:31,542 --> 00:31:36,459
His color, character symbol,
whatever I have.

360
00:31:36,584 --> 00:31:39,041
All that is you itself.

361
00:31:39,042 --> 00:31:41,416
Why are you asking
me all this today?

362
00:31:41,417 --> 00:31:45,541
Grandma, I need five
thousand rupees.

363
00:31:45,542 --> 00:31:49,957
Five thousand rupees?
- Aren't they a lot?

364
00:31:49,958 --> 00:31:53,416
Where have you asked a lot ever?

365
00:31:53,417 --> 00:31:56,708
I have always have had
less to give you.

366
00:31:58,417 --> 00:32:03,417
Why do you want them?

367
00:32:03,459 --> 00:32:05,541
Grandma, I will buy such
a thing for you...

368
00:32:05,542 --> 00:32:08,041
...Looking at which you
will be very happy.

369
00:32:08,042 --> 00:32:11,958
Son, I become happy
looking at you happy.

370
00:32:12,500 --> 00:32:15,416
See, my investments
will open next week.

371
00:32:15,417 --> 00:32:21,291
I will take that and give
it to you. Okay?

372
00:32:35,542 --> 00:32:38,416
You work here?
- It's a part time job.

373
00:32:38,417 --> 00:32:41,540
Pocket money with training too.
- Yes.

374
00:32:41,541 --> 00:32:43,582
Your nose!
- It is a bit different, isn't it?

375
00:32:43,583 --> 00:32:47,416
It is similar to papa's.
- No, it has become black.

376
00:32:47,417 --> 00:32:52,834
Just a minute, I will clean it.

377
00:32:56,417 --> 00:33:00,624
Your papa's nose seems too good.

378
00:33:00,625 --> 00:33:02,374
How did you come here?

379
00:33:02,375 --> 00:33:07,583
I don't know. My car stops suddenly.
- I will rectify it right away.

380
00:33:08,375 --> 00:33:10,874
It seems that you haven't serviced
your car since a long time.

381
00:33:10,875 --> 00:33:16,291
I don't know. I never
saw it before this.

382
00:33:16,917 --> 00:33:20,625
How do you do your studies
and part time job together?

383
00:33:20,750 --> 00:33:23,791
I manage it.
- Doesn't this hamper your studies?

384
00:33:23,917 --> 00:33:26,749
It does, but what can I do? There
isn't anyone to earn at home.

385
00:33:26,750 --> 00:33:29,416
After my mom's demise in childhood,
I had my papa...

386
00:33:29,417 --> 00:33:33,832
...and he expired in a car accident.

387
00:33:33,833 --> 00:33:37,459
Do you stay alone now?
- No. I have my grandma with me.

388
00:33:40,750 --> 00:33:43,416
Here, your car is rectified.

389
00:33:43,417 --> 00:33:45,749
What is the cost?
- Money? What money?

390
00:33:45,750 --> 00:33:48,582
I have just tightened a screw.
And you thanked me.

391
00:33:48,583 --> 00:33:50,832
That is a lot itself. - No. You
will have to take the money.

392
00:33:50,833 --> 00:33:53,582
At hour place, we don't charge
for tightening the screws.

393
00:33:53,583 --> 00:33:55,416
If you ever have some
major work, don't...

394
00:33:55,417 --> 00:33:57,540
...take any tension I will
do everything for free.

395
00:33:57,541 --> 00:34:03,166
Bring your car sometime later,
I will have it serviced too.

396
00:34:12,625 --> 00:34:16,541
If you do like this, I will stand
on the street and do like this.

397
00:34:16,750 --> 00:34:18,749
What did you say to that girl?

398
00:34:18,750 --> 00:34:21,416
If it is some major job,
you will do it for free?

399
00:34:21,417 --> 00:34:24,583
You work taking thank you? Do it!

400
00:34:25,083 --> 00:34:27,416
Instead of giving you money
in your envelope...

401
00:34:27,417 --> 00:34:29,416
...while giving you your salary,
I will write a thank you to you.

402
00:34:29,417 --> 00:34:30,999
But uncle...
- Shut up!

403
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,999
Why didn't you take
money from that girl?

404
00:34:33,000 --> 00:34:35,416
Is this a charitable garage?

405
00:34:35,417 --> 00:34:38,458
I pay fifteen mechanics
to tighten screws.

406
00:34:38,750 --> 00:34:42,792
When a car enters in this garage,
the charge is five hundred rupees.

407
00:34:42,917 --> 00:34:44,457
Uncle. I knew her.

408
00:34:44,458 --> 00:34:47,415
If you knew her, go home
and tighten her screws.

409
00:34:47,416 --> 00:34:50,458
If you tighten screws here,
I will loosen your screws.

410
00:34:50,583 --> 00:34:52,916
Uncle, this thing won't repeat.

411
00:34:52,917 --> 00:34:54,540
See. I will cut your
five hundred rupees.

412
00:34:54,541 --> 00:34:55,999
And if you ever do something
like this...

413
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:59,415
...I will cut your whole
salary and sack you.

414
00:34:59,416 --> 00:35:00,916
Go, go and work.

415
00:35:00,917 --> 00:35:04,374
Yes, uncle.

416
00:35:04,375 --> 00:35:08,916
Yes, uncle.

417
00:35:11,708 --> 00:35:13,415
What are you doing?

418
00:35:13,416 --> 00:35:15,457
Papa, I am putting
oil in the engine.

419
00:35:15,458 --> 00:35:17,374
Oh! You son of an ass! This is not...

420
00:35:17,375 --> 00:35:20,374
...the bottle of a engine oil. It
is the bottle of Roohafza sorbet.

421
00:35:20,375 --> 00:35:22,374
Shut up!

422
00:35:22,375 --> 00:35:23,540
Yes, uncle?

423
00:35:23,541 --> 00:35:25,791
Close him in the boot of some car.
- But papa!

424
00:35:25,792 --> 00:35:27,791
He has started opening bonnets.

425
00:35:27,792 --> 00:35:30,875
How will I learn, papa?
- What are you learning?

426
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,749
You are putting all my eating
and drinks inside cars.

427
00:35:33,750 --> 00:35:36,415
Don't see any difference
between car and Kartar?

428
00:35:36,416 --> 00:35:40,415
Get lost from here!

429
00:35:40,416 --> 00:35:43,415
See, Raj. You hide and look
at her in the library.

430
00:35:43,416 --> 00:35:45,457
You risk your life to
return her purse.

431
00:35:45,458 --> 00:35:47,415
And you repair her car for free.

432
00:35:47,416 --> 00:35:49,916
And your expression says
that you like Priya.

433
00:35:49,917 --> 00:35:52,083
If you do like here, then tell her.

434
00:35:52,084 --> 00:35:53,749
See, it is the rose day tomorrow.

435
00:35:53,750 --> 00:35:55,415
You go and offer her
a rose tomorrow.

436
00:35:55,416 --> 00:36:00,333
If she does accept it, you
have got your answer.

437
00:36:00,334 --> 00:36:01,707
And what if she doesn't?

438
00:36:01,708 --> 00:36:03,749
She will throw the
rose at your face.

439
00:36:03,750 --> 00:36:09,374
But you won't be insulted
by that, understood?

440
00:36:09,375 --> 00:36:14,750
The idea is not that bad.

441
00:36:39,416 --> 00:36:42,958
Only Miss Oxford is worthy
of giving a rose this year.

442
00:36:43,416 --> 00:36:46,792
Will she take the rose? - Yes. -

443
00:36:46,917 --> 00:36:53,125
She will take all our four roses.
- Yes?

444
00:36:53,416 --> 00:36:56,666
Did you understand it?
- Yes, sir. - Now go.

445
00:36:56,667 --> 00:37:00,916
See, the batter has come too.

446
00:37:00,917 --> 00:37:03,540
See. What black and yellow
coat has he worn?

447
00:37:03,541 --> 00:37:04,874
He looks like a taxi.

448
00:37:04,875 --> 00:37:06,916
This yellow suit,
suites you very much.

449
00:37:06,917 --> 00:37:09,791
Okay, listen. Look at that.

450
00:37:09,792 --> 00:37:15,208
Go with confidence and
give her the rose.

451
00:37:28,375 --> 00:37:31,416
Is this for me?
- Yes, it is for you.

452
00:37:31,541 --> 00:37:35,333
How could you dare to
wish me rose day?

453
00:37:37,375 --> 00:37:39,540
I befriended you thinking that
you were a simple boy...

454
00:37:39,541 --> 00:37:41,832
...and you took this
meaning out of it?

455
00:37:41,833 --> 00:37:43,916
I didn't know that these
cat eyes look...

456
00:37:43,917 --> 00:37:49,417
...at me with this meaning
beneath these spectacles.

457
00:37:57,416 --> 00:38:02,582
What are you hiding?
- Nothing.

458
00:38:02,583 --> 00:38:04,499
Okay, come on. We will dance.

459
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:05,749
No, I don't know how to dance.

460
00:38:05,750 --> 00:38:07,499
Which competition is going
on here? Come on!

461
00:38:07,500 --> 00:38:11,332
But even then, I don't
know how to dance.

462
00:38:11,333 --> 00:38:12,916
Hey, what's this!

463
00:38:12,917 --> 00:38:17,457
The glass with the intoxication
pills has been taken by the battery!

464
00:38:17,458 --> 00:38:19,415
The plan is ruined!

465
00:38:19,416 --> 00:38:20,916
No, it is good.

466
00:38:20,917 --> 00:38:22,874
The battery will be
intoxicated now...

467
00:38:22,875 --> 00:38:24,499
...and he will act insolently
with her.

468
00:38:24,500 --> 00:38:28,250
Now Miss Oxford will slap
him and put him to a side.

469
00:38:51,500 --> 00:38:55,415
What happened, Raj?
- What happened?

470
00:38:55,416 --> 00:38:58,792
I will tell you what happened
right now. - Come on.

471
00:38:58,959 --> 00:39:01,999
I haven't come here to jog
wearing this yellow suit.

472
00:39:02,000 --> 00:39:05,416
You asked me what I
was hiding, isn't it?

473
00:39:06,333 --> 00:39:11,292
I was hiding this, this!

474
00:39:12,917 --> 00:39:17,542
I started loving you when I saw you
for the first time in the college.

475
00:39:20,333 --> 00:39:22,707
I started seeing you everywhere.

476
00:39:22,708 --> 00:39:25,707
I became so worthless in your love...

477
00:39:25,708 --> 00:39:27,707
...that I started to see
you in my grandma too.

478
00:39:27,708 --> 00:39:30,791
Even then, I didn't have strength
to express my love.

479
00:39:30,792 --> 00:39:35,958
Then my friend Vicky understood
my sickness.

480
00:39:35,959 --> 00:39:40,416
Vicky said, ' Raj, love is not
silent, love is violent! '

481
00:39:40,625 --> 00:39:43,541
Even I have become violent!

482
00:39:43,542 --> 00:39:48,750
Hey, black crows...

483
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:58,583
If you love me, accept it,
or throw it on my face.

484
00:39:59,416 --> 00:40:03,291
I will not be insulted. Even
this, my friend told me.

485
00:40:04,500 --> 00:40:08,625
Now, whether you love me or not,
I will tell everybody!

486
00:41:16,417 --> 00:41:20,291
'When I saw you, I felt like this.'

487
00:41:20,417 --> 00:41:24,458
'The magic of love set in my heart.'

488
00:41:24,583 --> 00:41:26,916
'The aroma was mixed in the air.'

489
00:41:26,917 --> 00:41:29,416
'The heart beats got a romance.'

490
00:41:29,417 --> 00:41:35,209
' My state was excited! '

491
00:42:07,625 --> 00:42:09,416
'Without you... '

492
00:42:09,417 --> 00:42:11,999
'Without you, I am not interested
in anything.'

493
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:16,458
'Without you... O beloved! O beloved!

494
00:42:16,667 --> 00:42:21,458
' I stopped and refuse my heart,
but it didn't agree! '

495
00:42:21,583 --> 00:42:25,792
'O beloved! O beloved! '

496
00:42:26,000 --> 00:42:34,458
' Ever since I got your love,
this is going on.'

497
00:43:17,667 --> 00:43:21,458
'There was some excitement
in these breaths, my love.'

498
00:43:21,584 --> 00:43:26,458
' My beloved! My beloved! '

499
00:43:26,584 --> 00:43:31,458
'Your dreams settled in
my eyes, my beloved! '

500
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:40,458
' I just ask God this now! '

501
00:43:40,584 --> 00:43:44,625
' I should not leave
your embrace now.'

502
00:44:42,750 --> 00:44:47,416
Hey, Raj. You here?

503
00:44:47,417 --> 00:44:52,292
Grandma said that I said a lot
about you last night in my sleep.

504
00:44:52,417 --> 00:44:55,625
You would have. You said
a lot in my presence too.

505
00:44:55,833 --> 00:44:57,082
What did I say?

506
00:44:57,083 --> 00:45:00,791
Sit in the car, I will tell you.

507
00:45:00,792 --> 00:45:02,915
Do you know? You had drunk
a lot yesterday.

508
00:45:02,916 --> 00:45:05,374
No. I haven't even touched
liquor till now.

509
00:45:05,375 --> 00:45:07,374
I think that someone did
some mischief with me.

510
00:45:07,375 --> 00:45:08,915
Someone had surely mixed
something in my drink.

511
00:45:08,916 --> 00:45:10,749
Whoever did this mischief
did a good thing.

512
00:45:10,750 --> 00:45:12,874
You seem so simple from inside...

513
00:45:12,875 --> 00:45:15,541
...but you are a rascal from inside.
- Rascal?

514
00:45:15,542 --> 00:45:18,374
Not a rascal and great rascal.
Do you know what you did?

515
00:45:18,375 --> 00:45:21,374
You danced and made everyone
else dance too.

516
00:45:21,375 --> 00:45:23,624
You dance very well.

517
00:45:23,625 --> 00:45:26,416
But you did one mistake.
- What?

518
00:45:26,417 --> 00:45:27,915
You know? You gave me your rose.

519
00:45:27,916 --> 00:45:30,416
But you snatched your neighbor's
rose and gave me.

520
00:45:30,417 --> 00:45:31,957
You expressed your love to
me in everyone's presence.

521
00:45:31,958 --> 00:45:34,416
And that too under intoxication?

522
00:45:34,417 --> 00:45:36,832
I didn't like this action of yours.

523
00:45:36,833 --> 00:45:39,416
You expressed your love,
but under intoxication?

524
00:45:39,417 --> 00:45:43,459
Love is expressed in all
sanity. Like this.

525
00:45:49,833 --> 00:45:54,458
Did you understand?

526
00:46:08,375 --> 00:46:11,458
I wanted to apologize to you
for yesterday's mistake.

527
00:46:11,459 --> 00:46:14,541
I thought that our friendship
would be over today too.

528
00:46:14,542 --> 00:46:18,458
But I have got you today.
- I had got you yesterday itself.

529
00:46:18,459 --> 00:46:21,374
Today is a very happy day for me.

530
00:46:21,375 --> 00:46:24,417
What I am going to buy
is my most loved thing.

531
00:46:24,542 --> 00:46:30,000
Most loved thing?
- Stop the car.

532
00:46:31,459 --> 00:46:32,915
What is here?

533
00:46:32,916 --> 00:46:35,624
That loved thing is here itself.

534
00:46:35,625 --> 00:46:39,416
Yes, let it come, let it come back.

535
00:46:39,417 --> 00:46:45,291
Attach it quickly. Will
you take the whole day?

536
00:46:46,417 --> 00:46:48,749
Hey, what are you doing,
where are you taking it?

537
00:46:48,750 --> 00:46:51,458
To melt it and make it into
iron. I have bought it.

538
00:46:51,459 --> 00:46:54,082
To melt it? But I was to buy it.
- I don't know that.

539
00:46:54,083 --> 00:46:59,125
Go and talk to Patel about it.

540
00:46:59,417 --> 00:47:00,832
Uncle, you sold this car!

541
00:47:00,833 --> 00:47:02,749
You said that you would
buy it in a week.

542
00:47:02,750 --> 00:47:04,332
It is the ten days today,
you didn't come.

543
00:47:04,333 --> 00:47:05,749
But uncle, the money could be
arranged last night itself.

544
00:47:05,750 --> 00:47:07,332
I came yesterday morning,
but you weren't there.

545
00:47:07,333 --> 00:47:08,541
But it is sold now.

546
00:47:08,542 --> 00:47:10,707
Take the car back from
him and give it to me.

547
00:47:10,708 --> 00:47:12,790
Take it back? How will
I take it back?

548
00:47:12,791 --> 00:47:15,541
He has given me the money.
He is my old client.

549
00:47:15,542 --> 00:47:21,959
I will err in my counting. You
go. Let me count the money.

550
00:47:23,375 --> 00:47:26,750
It is iron for you. But for me...
it is a priceless thing for me.

551
00:47:26,875 --> 00:47:29,374
You take all my money and... please...

552
00:47:29,375 --> 00:47:32,416
What is so special in this scrap
that you are so worried?

553
00:47:32,417 --> 00:47:35,584
This isn't scrap, Priya.
This is my papa's car.

554
00:47:35,708 --> 00:47:39,999
This is my papa's possession.
He loved it a lot.

555
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:43,417
Uncle, you want to make
iron out of a car.

556
00:47:43,666 --> 00:47:46,832
Any car of scrap will do for you.
Please give me this car.

557
00:47:46,833 --> 00:47:50,665
I beg you! I request you!

558
00:47:50,666 --> 00:47:56,792
Take this money and
give me this car.

559
00:47:57,083 --> 00:47:59,665
Okay, take this car.

560
00:47:59,666 --> 00:48:03,542
Our work is to melt iron. Not
to melt anyone's emotions.

561
00:48:05,334 --> 00:48:10,291
Give him this car.

562
00:48:26,459 --> 00:48:30,374
Grandma?

563
00:48:30,375 --> 00:48:33,374
Didn't I tell you that I would
bring something looking...

564
00:48:33,375 --> 00:48:36,417
...at which you will be happy?
Look at this, Papa's car.

565
00:48:58,750 --> 00:49:05,542
' I believe in you! '

566
00:49:05,666 --> 00:49:10,625
Come on, mother. You sit here.
And you sit here.

567
00:49:10,750 --> 00:49:16,042
One photo with my Tarzan.

568
00:49:25,625 --> 00:49:27,374
Grandma...

569
00:49:27,375 --> 00:49:32,917
For a moment, I thought
that you brought my son.

570
00:49:34,459 --> 00:49:36,374
Yes, grandma.

571
00:49:36,375 --> 00:49:40,750
When I saw it for the first time,
I thought that my papa was with me.

572
00:49:42,459 --> 00:49:45,750
I will make it now, grandma.
I will design it.

573
00:49:47,375 --> 00:49:50,957
I know that it will
cost a lot of money.

574
00:49:50,958 --> 00:49:52,749
But I will work day
and night for it.

575
00:49:52,750 --> 00:49:54,416
I will do overtime.

576
00:49:54,417 --> 00:49:56,916
I will make it such a car
with my mechanical skills...

577
00:49:56,917 --> 00:50:03,000
...and hard work that people
will be stunned.

578
00:50:04,500 --> 00:50:07,749
Granda, this is Priya.

579
00:50:07,750 --> 00:50:09,665
Greetings.
- Bless you.

580
00:50:09,666 --> 00:50:11,416
This is the same London
one, isn't it?

581
00:50:11,417 --> 00:50:13,832
About whom you were saying?
- Yes.

582
00:50:13,833 --> 00:50:19,291
You go inside, I will come.

583
00:50:26,417 --> 00:50:28,416
Who is there?

584
00:50:28,417 --> 00:50:29,999
I am Raj, uncle.

585
00:50:30,000 --> 00:50:32,874
Hey, you haven't gone home
so late in the night?

586
00:50:32,875 --> 00:50:34,749
You haven't gone home?
- I am doing overtime.

587
00:50:34,750 --> 00:50:37,416
If you do part time in the day
and overtime in the night...

588
00:50:37,417 --> 00:50:39,707
...when will you do your studies?

589
00:50:39,708 --> 00:50:42,416
I need money.

590
00:50:42,417 --> 00:50:46,375
What is the matter? Is there
some problem in the house?

591
00:50:46,500 --> 00:50:48,874
No, uncle.

592
00:50:48,875 --> 00:50:52,917
Son, barring Lakshmi and Kuber
everyone needs money.

593
00:50:53,417 --> 00:50:55,582
But what is so serious, for which...

594
00:50:55,583 --> 00:50:57,749
...you are ready to leave
your studies too?

595
00:50:57,750 --> 00:51:01,417
I had told you about my papa,
isn't it? He had a car.

596
00:51:01,541 --> 00:51:06,958
I have got it after twelve years.

597
00:51:16,417 --> 00:51:19,999
I want to make that car once again.

598
00:51:20,000 --> 00:51:25,792
Son, the kids of nowadays throw
their parents from the house.

599
00:51:27,416 --> 00:51:30,415
And you are doing such a sacrifice...

600
00:51:30,416 --> 00:51:36,125
...to save your father's memoirs?

601
00:51:36,416 --> 00:51:42,708
You make that car. I am
with you. And see son.

602
00:51:44,042 --> 00:51:46,749
You are doing some part
time in my garage...

603
00:51:46,750 --> 00:51:49,749
...you do that. Instead of the
over time in my garage...

604
00:51:49,750 --> 00:51:52,833
...you spend that time
making your car.

605
00:51:53,416 --> 00:51:59,833
I will pay you for the hours that
you put in making that car.

606
00:52:03,375 --> 00:52:06,415
All of us are mechanics.

607
00:52:06,416 --> 00:52:08,916
It is not only our profession
to rectify problems.

608
00:52:08,917 --> 00:52:14,083
It is also our religion.

609
00:52:44,875 --> 00:52:46,415
You didn't go to the camp?

610
00:52:46,416 --> 00:52:48,415
When you did go there,
what will I do there?

611
00:52:48,416 --> 00:52:50,415
I can't help you in
building the car.

612
00:52:50,416 --> 00:52:55,625
But I can be with you, isn't it?

613
00:53:16,667 --> 00:53:21,292
'You are my craze, you
are my ambition.'

614
00:53:21,416 --> 00:53:25,708
'You exist in my breaths,
you are my heart.'

615
00:53:25,792 --> 00:53:33,792
'You are the emotion attached
to my heart.'

616
00:53:54,750 --> 00:53:58,833
' My name, my work... '

617
00:54:22,500 --> 00:54:27,583
'Why did my heart beat
as soon as I saw you? '

618
00:54:29,500 --> 00:54:34,792
' My hopes increased, there
was a dream in my eyes.'

619
00:54:59,416 --> 00:55:04,250
'Our friendship is different
in this whole world.

620
00:55:05,959 --> 00:55:10,667
'There is a procession of
memoirs at every curve.'

621
00:56:36,000 --> 00:56:40,917
'The emotions are deep.
You and I know this.'

622
00:56:43,500 --> 00:56:48,458
'The relation is very delicate.
You and I know this.'

623
00:57:44,417 --> 00:57:47,583
Why are you tying this Tarzan?
- This car is named Tarzan.

624
00:57:48,417 --> 00:57:51,416
Yes. My dad had named
this car Tarzan.

625
00:57:51,417 --> 00:57:53,416
So, should we go on a
drive in this Tarzan?

626
00:57:53,417 --> 00:57:54,582
No, Priya.

627
00:57:54,583 --> 00:57:56,582
This car won't start now.
- Why?

628
00:57:56,583 --> 00:57:58,999
It's fuel pump has jammed
because of rust.

629
00:57:59,000 --> 00:58:00,916
I have tried a lot but
it didn't open up.

630
00:58:00,917 --> 00:58:04,582
I have spoken to uncle. He
will arrange something.

631
00:58:04,583 --> 00:58:08,332
Okay. Thank you.

632
00:58:08,333 --> 00:58:10,416
What happened, uncle?

633
00:58:10,417 --> 00:58:14,208
Son, I tried a lot.
I spoke to some...

634
00:58:14,333 --> 00:58:19,250
...people who keep old cars,
I asked scrap dealers...

635
00:58:19,375 --> 00:58:21,874
...nobody has it. That company...

636
00:58:21,875 --> 00:58:25,583
...has even stopped making
cars of that model.

637
00:58:27,375 --> 00:58:31,792
Therefore, son. It is difficult
to get that fuel pump.

638
00:58:34,375 --> 00:58:39,750
Now, you can only believe in God.

639
00:59:02,667 --> 00:59:04,582
Son, didn't you sleep?

640
00:59:04,583 --> 00:59:08,332
I am not feeling sleepy, grandma.

641
00:59:08,333 --> 00:59:10,833
Even after so much hard
work and tries...

642
00:59:10,834 --> 00:59:13,332
...the fuel pump couldn't
be got. I think...

643
00:59:13,333 --> 00:59:15,666
...that my Tarzan will
not be able to run now.

644
00:59:15,667 --> 00:59:17,332
Why will it not be able to work?

645
00:59:17,333 --> 00:59:21,625
If God didn't wish it, how
would you get this car?

646
00:59:21,750 --> 00:59:25,375
He gave you strength to make
such a beautiful car.

647
00:59:25,625 --> 00:59:29,583
Have faith in him. He will
show you some way out.

648
00:59:30,625 --> 00:59:36,833
Sleep, son. Sleep.

649
01:02:02,791 --> 01:02:04,374
Grandma!

650
01:02:04,375 --> 01:02:07,791
The fuel pump is made, grandma!
My Tarzan has started, grandma!

651
01:02:11,417 --> 01:02:12,832
Did you see that, son?

652
01:02:12,833 --> 01:02:15,416
The fuel pump was made by
God's grace, isn't it?

653
01:02:15,417 --> 01:02:17,749
There won't be such a
car in the whole world.

654
01:02:17,750 --> 01:02:23,125
Bless you! Bless you!

655
01:02:53,417 --> 01:02:56,874
Wow! What a car!

656
01:02:56,875 --> 01:03:01,458
Hey, this is not a car.
This is great!

657
01:03:01,459 --> 01:03:06,957
I haven't seen such
a car in my dreams!

658
01:03:06,958 --> 01:03:12,250
Hey! This is the battery!

659
01:03:12,375 --> 01:03:14,416
And he has Miss Oxford with him too.

660
01:03:14,417 --> 01:03:16,832
This is my papa's favorite
restaurant.

661
01:03:16,833 --> 01:03:20,374
Why, grandma? Didn't papa bring
you here often? - Yes, son.

662
01:03:20,375 --> 01:03:21,874
Hey, how did this happen?

663
01:03:21,875 --> 01:03:23,583
From a cycle to a car
all of a sudden?

664
01:03:23,584 --> 01:03:25,999
I see Miss Oxford's support in this.

665
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:28,583
Battery's state and face,
both have changed.

666
01:03:28,584 --> 01:03:33,749
He snatched the morsel
from our mouth.

667
01:03:33,750 --> 01:03:36,374
He is showing off a lot.

668
01:03:36,375 --> 01:03:39,500
Today, we will change his face.

669
01:03:43,375 --> 01:03:47,959
Come on!

670
01:03:53,417 --> 01:03:54,583
That's strange, battery.

671
01:03:54,584 --> 01:03:56,583
You have become Pran
from Kanhayalal.

672
01:03:56,584 --> 01:03:59,666
Is it Miss Oxford's backing,
or dad's insurance?

673
01:04:06,459 --> 01:04:12,500
You made this fool a foreigner.

674
01:04:13,375 --> 01:04:15,874
Don't do this two much and
three much in front of us.

675
01:04:15,875 --> 01:04:17,957
Or I will change the close
up of your face.

676
01:04:17,958 --> 01:04:21,624
What insolence is this? Leave her!
- Shut up! Old woman!

677
01:04:21,625 --> 01:04:24,749
Raj, no! Wait Raj!

678
01:04:24,750 --> 01:04:26,749
Grandma, he has insulted you!

679
01:04:26,750 --> 01:04:32,375
I will show them how
much is two and two.

680
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:35,625
I won't spare him!
- Leave me!

681
01:04:38,375 --> 01:04:39,541
Wait!

682
01:04:39,542 --> 01:04:41,749
Wait! Or else I will have
to call the police.

683
01:04:41,750 --> 01:04:43,832
Mother, you please take him.

684
01:04:43,833 --> 01:04:46,749
C'mon, dear - Wait!

685
01:04:46,750 --> 01:04:49,374
We are going. That's
it. We are going.

686
01:04:49,375 --> 01:04:53,416
Leave us.

687
01:04:53,417 --> 01:04:54,583
Wait!

688
01:04:54,584 --> 01:04:56,583
Where are you going? Are you
getting scared and running?

689
01:04:56,584 --> 01:04:59,874
Where are you hiding with women?
If you have the guts, come out!

690
01:04:59,875 --> 01:05:01,458
He has run away! That wretch!

691
01:05:01,459 --> 01:05:02,707
Don't worry.

692
01:05:02,708 --> 01:05:04,957
We will break him and
his car tomorrow...

693
01:05:04,958 --> 01:05:10,208
...morning, outside the college.

694
01:06:06,708 --> 01:06:09,041
The battery has insulted
us a lot today.

695
01:06:09,042 --> 01:06:10,707
If the guards hadn't
come in between...

696
01:06:10,708 --> 01:06:12,374
...I would have made
such a state of his...

697
01:06:12,375 --> 01:06:15,374
...he wouldn't have faced
us throughout his life.

698
01:06:15,375 --> 01:06:18,750
Hey, who is there? Shut
down the light!

699
01:06:18,958 --> 01:06:23,374
Hey, shut down the light!

700
01:06:23,375 --> 01:06:25,707
Hey, it is battery.

701
01:06:25,708 --> 01:06:29,250
It seems that he is unlucky. He has
come in the lion's claws himself.

702
01:06:29,375 --> 01:06:31,416
Come on, we will settle
his hands and legs.

703
01:06:31,417 --> 01:06:34,374
As it is, there isn't
any lame student...

704
01:06:34,375 --> 01:06:40,291
...in the college who
comes on crutches.

705
01:06:41,750 --> 01:06:42,874
Hey wait! Hey wait!

706
01:06:42,875 --> 01:06:45,540
Hey, where are you running!
Hey! Catch him! Fast.

707
01:06:45,541 --> 01:06:50,166
C'mon, hurry up!

708
01:07:00,583 --> 01:07:03,333
Where are you hiding, you coward?

709
01:07:03,334 --> 01:07:05,416
There he is. Behind that pillar.

710
01:07:05,417 --> 01:07:08,833
Catch him. Don't let him escape.
- You Battery, wait there. Come out.

711
01:07:08,917 --> 01:07:11,416
Hey catch him.
- Where are you running to?

712
01:07:11,417 --> 01:07:13,874
Break its glass.
- But how?

713
01:07:13,875 --> 01:07:17,374
Throw your helmet into it.

714
01:07:17,375 --> 01:07:21,250
He thinks he's a hero. Catch him.
- We'll break his legs today.

715
01:07:21,375 --> 01:07:24,374
Why do you run, stop.
- I will break your limbs today.

716
01:07:24,375 --> 01:07:29,417
Maxi, catch him. Vicky,
don't let him get away.

717
01:07:34,375 --> 01:07:37,374
Stop!

718
01:07:37,375 --> 01:07:42,374
Are we chasing him
or he's chasing us?

719
01:07:42,375 --> 01:07:44,540
How did he come behind us?

720
01:07:44,541 --> 01:07:50,292
I am running out of gas.

721
01:07:59,500 --> 01:08:01,333
Hey you, son of a dog!

722
01:08:01,334 --> 01:08:05,333
Do you think you are very
smart sitting inside?

723
01:08:05,334 --> 01:08:10,875
Just come outside then you'll see
how I break you hands and legs.

724
01:08:13,917 --> 01:08:19,208
Hey, Battery threw
him in the gutters.

725
01:08:33,375 --> 01:08:36,374
He'll die.
- Someone should save him.

726
01:08:36,375 --> 01:08:38,374
You should go.
- No, you should go.

727
01:08:38,375 --> 01:08:40,874
You should go.
- You should go.

728
01:08:40,875 --> 01:08:43,374
Hey, go now.

729
01:08:43,375 --> 01:08:45,707
Bunty, are you alive?
- Yes, I'm alive.

730
01:08:45,708 --> 01:08:47,540
Open it, quickly. It stinks in here.

731
01:08:47,541 --> 01:08:52,750
Just hold your breath,
I'll be right there.

732
01:09:00,334 --> 01:09:04,875
Help me.

733
01:09:33,708 --> 01:09:34,874
I never thought, that Battery...

734
01:09:34,875 --> 01:09:40,083
...would turn out to be
so dangerous. - Yes.

735
01:09:40,875 --> 01:09:43,540
What are you doing up there?
- Come down soon.

736
01:09:43,541 --> 01:09:45,957
Where is Battery?

737
01:09:45,958 --> 01:09:50,374
What is this shh?

738
01:09:50,375 --> 01:09:51,707
Why are you banging your head?

739
01:09:51,708 --> 01:09:53,540
Can't you speak, you baldy?
Have you become dumb?

740
01:09:53,541 --> 01:09:57,792
Baldy, get down. Got dumb? And
why are you crying?

741
01:09:57,875 --> 01:10:00,666
Have you gone mad? Where
is that Battery?

742
01:10:00,667 --> 01:10:05,292
Run!

743
01:10:05,375 --> 01:10:08,374
Get inside!

744
01:10:08,375 --> 01:10:13,292
There!

745
01:10:13,833 --> 01:10:19,292
Hey, what are you doing?
- My hands are stuck.

746
01:10:19,375 --> 01:10:23,666
Who is it? - I think someone
is coming. Hide here.

747
01:10:23,667 --> 01:10:27,415
Run!

748
01:10:27,416 --> 01:10:30,625
We are stuck! Pull!

749
01:10:33,416 --> 01:10:35,415
How did you two get in?

750
01:10:35,416 --> 01:10:38,833
Hello uncle. We two got stuck
to each other. Please, help us.

751
01:10:38,917 --> 01:10:42,707
You spilled all my fevicol? - No,
we didn't. It got spilled by itself.

752
01:10:42,708 --> 01:10:44,832
We are stuck together. Separate us.

753
01:10:44,833 --> 01:10:47,582
Now I'll stick you
two in such a way...

754
01:10:47,583 --> 01:10:53,500
...as we stick ply to wood.

755
01:10:57,875 --> 01:10:59,916
Enough Raj, don't come ahead.

756
01:10:59,917 --> 01:11:01,874
Or else the car will run over us.

757
01:11:01,875 --> 01:11:04,540
No Raj. - You have squeezed
out our hooliganism.

758
01:11:04,541 --> 01:11:07,540
And only we know from
where it came out.

759
01:11:07,541 --> 01:11:09,874
No Raj. We didn't know that
if we say something...

760
01:11:09,875 --> 01:11:11,916
...to your granny then you'll
become so violent.

761
01:11:11,917 --> 01:11:15,374
Please, spare us, Raj.
- Forgive us, Raj.

762
01:11:15,375 --> 01:11:17,707
Please, we beg of you.
- Forgive us, Raj.

763
01:11:17,708 --> 01:11:24,125
We'll never do this again.
We are sorry.

764
01:11:26,833 --> 01:11:29,832
We are saved.

765
01:11:29,833 --> 01:11:35,292
We had so much of fun.

766
01:11:39,416 --> 01:11:45,167
Raj? What a car Raj has brought!

767
01:11:46,875 --> 01:11:50,415
I've never even seen
such a car in books.

768
01:11:50,416 --> 01:11:52,415
I made this car after
thinking that only.

769
01:11:52,416 --> 01:11:54,415
Your whole life is set, pal.
After finishing college...

770
01:11:54,416 --> 01:11:56,415
...you start your own workshop.
And design such...

771
01:11:56,416 --> 01:11:58,415
...beautiful cars in it. Just
watch as all the automobile...

772
01:11:58,416 --> 01:12:03,916
...companies will have to
pull down their shutters.

773
01:12:05,458 --> 01:12:07,374
Raj, if you meet Rocky
and his friends...

774
01:12:07,375 --> 01:12:09,541
...then just stay away from them.
- Why?

775
01:12:09,542 --> 01:12:12,374
Any problems?
- Yes.

776
01:12:12,375 --> 01:12:18,083
Brother Raj!
- Brother Raj!

777
01:12:21,667 --> 01:12:24,541
Brother Raj, please forgive us.

778
01:12:24,542 --> 01:12:25,958
What has happened to you all?

779
01:12:25,959 --> 01:12:27,541
Didn't brother Raj
tell you anything?

780
01:12:27,542 --> 01:12:29,541
What would I tell? I
don't know anything.

781
01:12:29,542 --> 01:12:32,541
You don't know? Even we don't know.

782
01:12:32,542 --> 01:12:34,374
We all have forgotten everything.

783
01:12:34,375 --> 01:12:37,374
You didn't kill us, isn't
that a big favor itself?

784
01:12:37,375 --> 01:12:39,541
Raj, did you do all this?
- Forget it, sister Priya.

785
01:12:39,542 --> 01:12:41,415
With the evil intentions
we use to see you...

786
01:12:41,416 --> 01:12:43,707
...now we'll never see
you that way again.

787
01:12:43,708 --> 01:12:46,415
If any of our eyes survive
then we'll see...

788
01:12:46,416 --> 01:12:48,749
...you mother with one eye
and sister with the other.

789
01:12:48,750 --> 01:12:50,749
If we had one more eye
then we would have...

790
01:12:50,750 --> 01:12:53,041
...saw you as grandmother.
But we don't have any.

791
01:12:53,042 --> 01:12:54,749
Did you see? This happens when...

792
01:12:54,750 --> 01:12:56,916
...a decent guy looses his decency.

793
01:12:56,917 --> 01:12:59,415
A decent guy loosing his
decency and becomes...

794
01:12:59,416 --> 01:13:01,707
...so dangerous, this is the
first time I have ever seen.

795
01:13:01,708 --> 01:13:04,374
Our hearts came up to our necks.

796
01:13:04,375 --> 01:13:08,250
You just say it once that go
away dogs, I forgive you.

797
01:13:08,375 --> 01:13:10,374
C'mon Raj, forgive them.

798
01:13:10,375 --> 01:13:12,707
C'mon now go into the class.
And don't let me watch you.

799
01:13:12,708 --> 01:13:15,791
Thank you, brother.
- May God always bless you.

800
01:13:15,792 --> 01:13:21,250
Just take care of yourself.
- Yes, move. C'mon!

801
01:14:25,667 --> 01:14:28,374
Yes Mr. Narang.

802
01:14:28,375 --> 01:14:30,374
You run your bulldozers
on their slums...

803
01:14:30,375 --> 01:14:31,708
...without any worries.

804
01:14:31,709 --> 01:14:34,374
I want that land to
be cleared in a week.

805
01:14:34,375 --> 01:14:37,458
I'm coming to Palghar tomorrow.
We'll discuss the rest there itself.

806
01:14:38,375 --> 01:14:40,541
Where are you getting the
bulldozers to run over?

807
01:14:40,542 --> 01:14:41,874
In a slum at Palghar.

808
01:14:41,875 --> 01:14:44,541
I'm constructing a two-wheeler
factory there on your name.

809
01:14:44,542 --> 01:14:47,625
Ladybird bicycle and moppet
company. Did you like it?

810
01:14:48,375 --> 01:14:50,708
This Four Fox company
will soon shut down.

811
01:14:50,709 --> 01:14:52,541
And my partners are thinking
of starting...

812
01:14:52,542 --> 01:14:54,708
...a business in poultry
and garments.

813
01:14:54,709 --> 01:14:56,416
That's why I thought, in your name...

814
01:14:56,417 --> 01:14:58,749
...I would bring up our
own empire and...

815
01:14:58,750 --> 01:15:04,375
...then throw my partners out
within 2-4 years. Let's go.

816
01:15:31,375 --> 01:15:34,374
Raj!
- Yes, uncle.

817
01:15:34,375 --> 01:15:36,374
Raj, go to Mr. Singhania's house.

818
01:15:36,375 --> 01:15:38,374
He's having car troubles.

819
01:15:38,375 --> 01:15:40,040
Uncle, Mr. Deepak's car's
windscreen need to be changed.

820
01:15:40,041 --> 01:15:42,874
And we have to deliver it today.
- I'll get that changed from Manglu.

821
01:15:42,875 --> 01:15:44,541
You take the towing car with you.

822
01:15:44,542 --> 01:15:46,708
If Mr. Singhania's car doesn't
gets fixed till evening...

823
01:15:46,709 --> 01:15:48,708
...then tow it to the garage. Go.
- Yes.

824
01:15:48,709 --> 01:15:50,457
Hey Golu.
- Yes papa.

825
01:15:50,458 --> 01:15:53,541
Go and tell Manglu to change Mr.
Deepak's car's windscreen.

826
01:15:53,542 --> 01:15:55,874
Which one should be fitted? Of
the fiat or of the ambassador?

827
01:15:55,875 --> 01:15:59,292
You mad fellow, how can you
fix some other windscreen?

828
01:15:59,417 --> 01:16:02,332
It can happen, papa. Lots of
people do this to save money.

829
01:16:02,333 --> 01:16:04,541
For example as today the fan belt
of D'souza's car was broken.

830
01:16:04,542 --> 01:16:06,374
So I told him, it'll
cost him Rs.110.

831
01:16:06,375 --> 01:16:08,374
But he said, no. He said
to use something cheaper.

832
01:16:08,375 --> 01:16:11,583
So do you know, I have attached
your pant's belt to it! - What?

833
01:16:11,709 --> 01:16:13,874
Yes. In the evening when you
wear it then you'll see...

834
01:16:13,875 --> 01:16:16,457
...that your pants would
keep on sliding down.

835
01:16:16,458 --> 01:16:20,374
Hey Manglu!
- Yes uncle.

836
01:16:20,375 --> 01:16:22,374
Manglu, take him and lock
him inside the house.

837
01:16:22,375 --> 01:16:28,250
Or else he'll get my garage
shut down. Take him. - C'mon.

838
01:16:35,500 --> 01:16:39,584
Welcome, Mr. Chopra. Seeing
you after such a long time.

839
01:16:40,375 --> 01:16:43,374
Uncle, the headlights of my car
are broken. Just change it.

840
01:16:43,375 --> 01:16:45,666
I have to go to Palghar and
return by night today.

841
01:16:45,667 --> 01:16:47,708
By the ways Mr. Chopra,
it's believed that...

842
01:16:47,709 --> 01:16:49,374
...it's lucky when glass breaks.

843
01:16:49,375 --> 01:16:51,708
I think you'll have a
very lucky day today.

844
01:16:51,709 --> 01:16:53,833
These are all superstitions,
Mr. Singh.

845
01:16:53,834 --> 01:16:56,374
If this was possible
then I would have...

846
01:16:56,375 --> 01:16:58,374
...lived in a glass house. And
would have messed with...

847
01:16:58,375 --> 01:17:02,332
...every crazy man carrying a stone.

848
01:17:02,333 --> 01:17:04,708
If he believes it's lucky
then it becomes lucky.

849
01:17:04,709 --> 01:17:07,541
If he believes it's unlucky
then it becomes unlucky.

850
01:17:07,542 --> 01:17:08,915
Let's see, what happens.

851
01:17:08,916 --> 01:17:13,625
Come Mr. Chopra. Until we fix your
car lets sit in the office.

852
01:18:49,709 --> 01:18:54,750
What are you doing?

853
01:19:13,333 --> 01:19:14,666
Hey, what are you doing?

854
01:19:14,667 --> 01:19:19,875
Changing lanes giving
the wrong signal?

855
01:20:16,708 --> 01:20:21,792
Hey, you'll get me killed!

856
01:20:42,875 --> 01:20:44,999
These kids are getting irritated
standing in this heat...

857
01:20:45,000 --> 01:20:46,832
...for the past 3 hours.
- What will we do for their food?

858
01:20:46,833 --> 01:20:48,915
We'll have to manage something.
We are very late.

859
01:20:48,916 --> 01:20:52,707
Hey, a car is coming.

860
01:20:52,708 --> 01:20:58,166
Stop!
- Please, stop!

861
01:21:09,375 --> 01:21:11,541
Look sir, we have been troubled
since the past 3 hours.

862
01:21:11,542 --> 01:21:15,374
Our bus is stuck. Please, help us.

863
01:21:15,375 --> 01:21:18,625
C'mon kids, get into
the bus. Hurry up.

864
01:22:17,375 --> 01:22:22,375
Hey, what are you doing?

865
01:23:42,500 --> 01:23:46,791
It'll kill me! Someone save me.

866
01:25:36,209 --> 01:25:38,540
It's a very interesting funda.

867
01:25:38,541 --> 01:25:40,291
The crossing is broken
over there and...

868
01:25:40,292 --> 01:25:42,208
...the car is found burnt here.

869
01:25:42,209 --> 01:25:47,041
Even the body has been
burned to death.

870
01:25:47,042 --> 01:25:49,124
The entire area should
undergo proper...

871
01:25:49,125 --> 01:25:54,375
...forensic analysis and
detailed checking.

872
01:25:55,167 --> 01:25:57,041
This accident happened
due to this crossing.

873
01:25:57,042 --> 01:25:58,540
The breaks of the car
was not working...

874
01:25:58,541 --> 01:26:00,041
...so it broke the crossing,
rammed into the train...

875
01:26:00,042 --> 01:26:01,457
...and fell in the open ground
after blowing up.

876
01:26:01,458 --> 01:26:02,999
You are a gatemen.
Didn't you notice?

877
01:26:03,000 --> 01:26:04,415
If there would have been
a flyover here then...

878
01:26:04,416 --> 01:26:05,999
...the car wouldn't have
rammed into the train.

879
01:26:06,000 --> 01:26:07,499
Why don't you built a flyover
over the crossing?

880
01:26:07,500 --> 01:26:09,249
Constable, we don't have any funds.

881
01:26:09,250 --> 01:26:12,124
The railway is suffering a loss.
- Even I travel by train.

882
01:26:12,125 --> 01:26:15,083
After booking the tickets
before 2 months...

883
01:26:15,084 --> 01:26:17,916
...240 passengers are stuffed
into a 40 passenger coach.

884
01:26:17,917 --> 01:26:19,415
And you are saying the railway
is suffering a loss.

885
01:26:19,416 --> 01:26:20,916
But sir why are you
telling me all this?

886
01:26:20,917 --> 01:26:22,249
Tell that to the government.
- Where is the government?

887
01:26:22,250 --> 01:26:25,041
Call him now.
- What?

888
01:26:25,042 --> 01:26:27,332
Sir, I have found out that
this is a useless case.

889
01:26:27,333 --> 01:26:28,916
You are unnecessarily
standing in the heat.

890
01:26:28,917 --> 01:26:30,415
Consider this as an accident
case. Close its file.

891
01:26:30,416 --> 01:26:34,041
Cool your head with ice and
rest at the police station.

892
01:26:34,042 --> 01:26:39,000
Sir, we have found tire marks of
some other car with this car.

893
01:26:41,209 --> 01:26:45,042
That means my suspicions are right.
This is a murder case...

894
01:26:45,125 --> 01:26:49,042
...which has been tried to
be covered as an accident.

895
01:26:52,042 --> 01:26:55,374
Now this case is in charge
of Mr. Khurana.

896
01:26:55,375 --> 01:26:58,499
Now the murderer's funda
won't work any more.

897
01:26:58,500 --> 01:27:01,166
Now Khurana's stick
will do all the work.

898
01:27:01,167 --> 01:27:04,124
Listen! - Yes sir. - I want the
chassis number of this car...

899
01:27:04,125 --> 01:27:07,250
...and the postmortem report
of this dead body, urgently.

900
01:27:08,209 --> 01:27:14,292
From that we'll know
who the deceased was.

901
01:27:16,458 --> 01:27:18,083
Mrs. Chopra, you are saying...

902
01:27:18,084 --> 01:27:20,208
...there weren't any threatening
calls for extortions.

903
01:27:20,209 --> 01:27:21,582
But without enmity, without reason...

904
01:27:21,583 --> 01:27:23,208
...no one would murder someone.

905
01:27:23,209 --> 01:27:26,833
Inspector, he didn't
have any enemies.

906
01:27:27,209 --> 01:27:30,875
My husband was a very humane
and God like person.

907
01:27:32,250 --> 01:27:35,333
This is a strange generation.
Even God's are being murdered.

908
01:27:35,416 --> 01:27:39,041
They should also receive security.

909
01:27:39,042 --> 01:27:42,124
Alka, take sister-in-law inside.

910
01:27:42,125 --> 01:27:46,499
Who is this lame fellow?

911
01:27:46,500 --> 01:27:51,875
What do you think can be the reason
for your partner's murder?

912
01:27:51,959 --> 01:27:53,958
What can we say, inspector?

913
01:27:53,959 --> 01:27:57,000
Since our brother like
partner has died...

914
01:27:57,125 --> 01:28:00,917
...if we even drink water then
it would come out as tears.

915
01:28:01,042 --> 01:28:03,540
It's the latest news.

916
01:28:03,541 --> 01:28:06,958
Daddy that...
- Shut up.

917
01:28:06,959 --> 01:28:11,166
Inspector, for him every
thing is latest.

918
01:28:11,167 --> 01:28:12,916
The inquiry has begun.

919
01:28:12,917 --> 01:28:19,375
If you people get to know something
then tell us about it.

920
01:28:20,208 --> 01:28:22,541
This is a new funda.

921
01:28:22,542 --> 01:28:24,083
When we were talking then...

922
01:28:24,084 --> 01:28:26,916
...what was the need
to speak in between?

923
01:28:26,917 --> 01:28:28,207
What's the latest news?

924
01:28:28,208 --> 01:28:31,916
Once I had heard you two talking.
- What?

925
01:28:31,917 --> 01:28:33,541
That Chopra should be
killed like dogs.

926
01:28:33,542 --> 01:28:35,916
What was the need to say it
in front of that inspector?

927
01:28:35,917 --> 01:28:37,582
So that the killers
get caught very soon.

928
01:28:37,583 --> 01:28:39,541
Anthony, what son have
you given birth to?

929
01:28:39,542 --> 01:28:41,582
Now explain him. He'll get
the both of us trapped.

930
01:28:41,583 --> 01:28:45,457
Go and get the car ready, Jojo. Go!

931
01:28:45,458 --> 01:28:47,207
Everything is ruined.
- What?

932
01:28:47,208 --> 01:28:49,124
Today there was a New Year's
party and this Chopra...

933
01:28:49,125 --> 01:28:51,124
...has flopped all our plans.
It would have been so nice...

934
01:28:51,125 --> 01:28:53,958
...if he would have
died after 4 days.

935
01:28:53,959 --> 01:28:55,457
At least we would have
enjoyed in the evening.

936
01:28:55,458 --> 01:28:58,207
Why won't we enjoy? He
wasn't our brother.

937
01:28:58,208 --> 01:29:01,333
He was a fraud partner. We
have given our condolences.

938
01:29:01,458 --> 01:29:04,374
We have cried our hearts out in
front of his photo for 45 minutes.

939
01:29:04,375 --> 01:29:07,499
Do you want to continue this,
your whole life?

940
01:29:07,500 --> 01:29:09,041
One of the partners of
the Four Fox company...

941
01:29:09,042 --> 01:29:11,499
...has left this country. The
other has left this world.

942
01:29:11,500 --> 01:29:13,874
And the remaining are we two.
Partners by fifty-fifty.

943
01:29:13,875 --> 01:29:19,125
In this joy we'll celebrate
the New year today.

944
01:29:52,208 --> 01:29:55,834
'Lf love is a mistake... '

945
01:30:02,291 --> 01:30:07,333
'... then I'll definitely
do it. Oh beautiful! '

946
01:30:19,166 --> 01:30:22,291
'Lf deaths is it's penalty... '

947
01:30:25,000 --> 01:30:30,291
'... then I'll definitely
die. Oh beautiful! '

948
01:30:51,542 --> 01:30:54,082
Manager, I left my beautiful
wife at home...

949
01:30:54,083 --> 01:30:56,249
...with an excuse for a conference.
- Have you made...

950
01:30:56,250 --> 01:30:59,374
...any special arrangements
for the New year's party?

951
01:30:59,375 --> 01:31:01,916
I have made such arrangements that...

952
01:31:01,917 --> 01:31:04,290
...both your hearts will
be pleased with it.

953
01:31:04,291 --> 01:31:09,334
Come in and see the fun.

954
01:31:35,041 --> 01:31:39,457
'I'm in your love.'

955
01:31:39,458 --> 01:31:44,625
'I'm in your heart's passion.'

956
01:31:48,208 --> 01:31:52,500
'I got robbed, I got ruined,
I got killed, oh beloved.'

957
01:31:54,458 --> 01:31:58,834
'Don't know what will happen to me? '

958
01:31:59,375 --> 01:32:04,500
'The intoxication of your lips... '

959
01:32:05,041 --> 01:32:09,917
'... I'll definitely taste
it. Oh beautiful! '

960
01:32:42,542 --> 01:32:47,374
'You are my dream.'

961
01:32:47,375 --> 01:32:52,500
'My heart is restless.'

962
01:32:56,041 --> 01:33:00,500
'You are in my heart, my life
and my soul, oh beloved.'

963
