1199
01:54:39,875 --> 01:54:41,207
Have you gone nuts?

1200
01:54:41,208 --> 01:54:43,874
Is this car some crab, that
can walk on its sides?

1201
01:54:43,875 --> 01:54:45,499
How can he barge in
such a small space?

1202
01:54:45,500 --> 01:54:47,999
He must be waiting too
long in the queue.

1203
01:54:48,000 --> 01:54:51,999
Hey truck driver, take
the truck ahead.

1204
01:54:52,000 --> 01:54:56,792
C'mon, keep moving ahead.

1205
01:55:00,042 --> 01:55:04,875
Hey, bring it forward.

1206
01:55:07,250 --> 01:55:11,041
It's a nice car. Is it imported?

1207
01:55:11,042 --> 01:55:12,416
No sir, I have built it myself.

1208
01:55:12,417 --> 01:55:16,458
So, you have built it.
C'mon get out.

1209
01:55:16,459 --> 01:55:19,041
Heroin is transported in such cars.

1210
01:55:19,042 --> 01:55:20,916
Sir, which heroine
has been kidnapped?

1211
01:55:20,917 --> 01:55:24,041
I'm not talking about heroine
but heroin. Drugs!

1212
01:55:24,042 --> 01:55:26,249
C'mon, open the trunk of the car.
- No sir, there's nothing in it.

1213
01:55:26,250 --> 01:55:29,624
All say the same thing. I
feel this car is trouble.

1214
01:55:29,625 --> 01:55:34,500
C'mon, open the trunk of the car.

1215
01:55:34,500 --> 01:55:39,041
Not the glass, open the trunk.
- I'm doing the same, sir.

1216
01:55:39,042 --> 01:55:42,167
Sir, I'll check.
- No, I'll check.

1217
01:55:49,208 --> 01:55:55,042
Get me out!
- Sir, wait! Pull!

1218
01:56:00,500 --> 01:56:06,667
Don't pull me. Open the trunk.

1219
01:56:07,666 --> 01:56:11,292
I'm dead! What's happening?
It's too much of pain.

1220
01:56:12,042 --> 01:56:16,582
C'mon, take your car and get out.
- Get lost.

1221
01:56:16,583 --> 01:56:18,208
Call for the doctor.
- Yes.

1222
01:56:18,209 --> 01:56:23,667
Take this omen car away from here.
- Go away.

1223
01:56:27,042 --> 01:56:28,916
Sir, did you get hurt?

1224
01:56:28,917 --> 01:56:31,333
Shut up! First tell
me who pulled my leg?

1225
01:56:31,334 --> 01:56:32,416
I didn't pull it.
- Nor did I pull it.

1226
01:56:32,417 --> 01:56:36,874
Then who pulled it.

1227
01:56:36,875 --> 01:56:42,542
Here comes the slow poke.
- Finally?

1228
01:56:48,209 --> 01:56:49,957
Do you know there was too much
of checking on the highway.

1229
01:56:49,958 --> 01:56:55,375
There was long queue.
- You forget all that and get ready.

1230
01:57:33,209 --> 01:57:37,000
That nuisance car jammed my neck
just like a rusted steering.

1231
01:57:42,375 --> 01:57:48,500
Hey, from where did this come?

1232
01:57:49,958 --> 01:57:54,957
You dare to dash a policeman's jeep!

1233
01:57:54,958 --> 01:58:00,500
Where did go? It just vanished
in to thin air!

1234
01:58:03,958 --> 01:58:08,916
Hey, have you gone nuts?

1235
01:58:18,917 --> 01:58:22,458
You have messed with me! Now,
I won't leave you.

1236
01:58:28,541 --> 01:58:30,916
Get out from the car.

1237
01:58:30,917 --> 01:58:35,540
Get out from the car or else I'll
kill you in an encounter.

1238
01:58:35,541 --> 01:58:39,249
You try to intimidate me!

1239
01:58:39,250 --> 01:58:42,374
You try to intimidate an
policeman and run showing your back.

1240
01:58:42,375 --> 01:58:45,916
Hey, stop! I insist
that you stop. Stop!

1241
01:58:45,917 --> 01:58:48,374
Hey, will you stop?

1242
01:58:48,375 --> 01:58:51,916
I'll break all your
bones. Hey, stop!

1243
01:58:51,917 --> 01:58:55,375
Are you a man or an animal?
Stop, man. Stop!

1244
01:58:55,458 --> 01:59:00,750
You bastard! Why doesn't it stop?

1245
01:59:04,209 --> 01:59:05,957
You started running again.

1246
01:59:05,958 --> 01:59:10,041
You dare to make a policeman
run after you!

1247
01:59:10,042 --> 01:59:12,208
You make a heavy man like me to run.

1248
01:59:12,209 --> 01:59:14,374
Just let me get hold of
you. I'll kill you...

1249
01:59:14,375 --> 01:59:20,292
...just like a bug is pulled out
from the chair and smashed.

1250
01:59:27,333 --> 01:59:30,792
When I fired in the air one time...
...you came to your senses!

1251
01:59:30,917 --> 01:59:35,667
Now, get out from here.

1252
01:59:39,250 --> 01:59:43,167
Goodness me! There's no one in here.

1253
01:59:57,917 --> 02:00:00,374
Hey, this car is moving
without a driver.

1254
02:00:00,375 --> 02:00:04,250
Hey, what are you doing? Why are
you making me run backwards?

1255
02:00:04,375 --> 02:00:07,874
Let me see, what's behind. You
make a policeman run backwards.

1256
02:00:07,875 --> 02:00:12,166
Hey, you'll hurt me! You'll
hurt me. What are you doing?

1257
02:00:12,167 --> 02:00:14,874
I can't even see, what's
going on behind.

1258
02:00:14,875 --> 02:00:19,417
Stop, at once!

1259
02:00:32,917 --> 02:00:35,959
Hey, you all don't move from here.
Or else, I'll become the scapegoat.

1260
02:01:20,167 --> 02:01:25,625
Run from here. Run! Run
from here, quickly.

1261
02:01:27,875 --> 02:01:29,207
Hey, where's the key, man?

1262
02:01:29,208 --> 02:01:31,999
It seems it got lost when
the jeep overturned.

1263
02:01:32,000 --> 02:01:34,166
What will I do, now? I'll sneak
in through the garage.

1264
02:01:34,167 --> 02:01:39,459
I'll get in through the garage.

1265
02:01:54,208 --> 02:01:57,333
Goodness me! This reached here, too!

1266
02:03:00,917 --> 02:03:02,415
C'mon. Fast! Fast!

1267
02:03:02,416 --> 02:03:05,207
Hello, headquarters. This
is Vijay. I mean Ajay.

1268
02:03:05,208 --> 02:03:08,250
I forgot my own name. I'm
inspector Sanjay Sharma.

1269
02:03:08,375 --> 02:03:11,374
A Mumbai car is hell-bent
on taking my life.

1270
02:03:11,375 --> 02:03:15,250
The number of that
car is MH-01-M-37.

1271
02:03:15,458 --> 02:03:21,250
And the most startling
fact is that the car...

1272
02:03:41,208 --> 02:03:44,207
Now, we want to hear
good news from you.

1273
02:03:44,208 --> 02:03:47,916
From us?
- Or else, from whom?

1274
02:03:47,917 --> 02:03:53,292
Thanks for coming, buddy.

1275
02:03:59,208 --> 02:04:00,416
What is this inspector?

1276
02:04:00,417 --> 02:04:03,416
Anyone is being killed!
Anyone is being murdered!

1277
02:04:03,417 --> 02:04:05,249
Not anyone, Mr. D'costa.

1278
02:04:05,250 --> 02:04:07,249
Only those people are being killed...

1279
02:04:07,250 --> 02:04:09,290
...whose funda is related to you.

1280
02:04:09,291 --> 02:04:12,750
Mr. Sharma and Mr. Chopra
were both your partners.

1281
02:04:12,875 --> 02:04:15,874
After investigation it has been
revealed that even inspector...

1282
02:04:15,875 --> 02:04:18,249
...Sanjay Sharma had an old
connection with you.

1283
02:04:18,250 --> 02:04:19,416
This is the latest news.

1284
02:04:19,417 --> 02:04:21,374
This means that dad is
fourth on the list.

1285
02:04:21,375 --> 02:04:23,416
Shut up! What nonsense
are you talking?

1286
02:04:23,417 --> 02:04:26,874
Mr. D'costa, he's right.

1287
02:04:26,875 --> 02:04:29,207
The way in which your mates
have been murdered...

1288
02:04:29,208 --> 02:04:31,416
...it seems that even you
can be on the hit list.

1289
02:04:31,417 --> 02:04:34,416
That's why, I'd suggest you
to take police protection.

1290
02:04:34,417 --> 02:04:36,874
Yes, Mr. D'costa. Take
police protection.

1291
02:04:36,875 --> 02:04:39,374
Or else you'll die a vague death.
- Good gracious!

1292
02:04:39,375 --> 02:04:42,207
Because that car runs over
you and breaks your bones.

1293
02:04:42,208 --> 02:04:44,416
And bones don't get
joined in old age.

1294
02:04:44,417 --> 02:04:45,624
He gives you such a death...

1295
02:04:45,625 --> 02:04:47,541
...that any witness gets
frightened to death!

1296
02:04:47,542 --> 02:04:50,874
No! No, inspector,
please save my dad.

1297
02:04:50,875 --> 02:04:53,290
There's no one for me in
this world besides him.

1298
02:04:53,291 --> 02:04:55,416
Dad, please don't go away
leaving me alone.

1299
02:04:55,417 --> 02:04:58,207
I'll become an orphan, dad.

1300
02:04:58,208 --> 02:05:01,916
Shut up! I'm still alive.

1301
02:05:01,917 --> 02:05:03,916
Why don't you arrest
the killer instead...

1302
02:05:03,917 --> 02:05:05,416
...of giving me protection?

1303
02:05:05,417 --> 02:05:07,207
This is the funda.

1304
02:05:07,208 --> 02:05:10,834
I don't have any evidence to
prove that Raj is the killer.

1305
02:05:11,208 --> 02:05:13,916
I can't give you anything
except protection.

1306
02:05:13,917 --> 02:05:17,500
Whenever you need the
police you can call me.

1307
02:05:18,917 --> 02:05:24,500
Stay indoors. Don't venture
out in the open.

1308
02:05:25,917 --> 02:05:28,124
Jojo, you always frighten me.

1309
02:05:28,125 --> 02:05:30,124
I get scared, seeing you get scared.

1310
02:05:30,125 --> 02:05:32,124
No, dad. I get scared,
seeing you get scared.

1311
02:05:32,125 --> 02:05:34,332
All right then. We'll
not get scared anymore.

1312
02:05:34,333 --> 02:05:39,334
We'll fight back with courage.

1313
02:05:40,041 --> 02:05:42,124
Dad, he's come?
- Who?

1314
02:05:42,125 --> 02:05:45,957
Your killer!
- Killer? - Yes.

1315
02:05:45,958 --> 02:05:48,040
Hey dad, wait for me.

1316
02:05:48,041 --> 02:05:51,417
Hey, monkey. Down. Let
me close it. It's done.

1317
02:05:55,208 --> 02:05:57,957
Why are you closing the door?

1318
02:05:57,958 --> 02:05:59,207
Where should I hide?

1319
02:05:59,208 --> 02:06:02,957
Hey, fool! You left
me stranded there!

1320
02:06:02,958 --> 02:06:05,374
What, dad?
- Yes. - You made such a big house.

1321
02:06:05,375 --> 02:06:07,207
You didn't even make at
least one place to hide.

1322
02:06:07,208 --> 02:06:08,916
Now, when that killer
is coming to kill you...

1323
02:06:08,917 --> 02:06:10,916
...then, where shall I hide?

1324
02:06:10,917 --> 02:06:14,500
Fool! He's coming to kill
me and you are hiding.

1325
02:06:14,917 --> 02:06:17,082
Go. If you are really my son...
- No!

1326
02:06:17,083 --> 02:06:19,915
...then go and finish the enemy.

1327
02:06:19,916 --> 02:06:25,207
Go. Go, you worthless fellow.

1328
02:06:25,208 --> 02:06:28,875
Oh God, where shall I hide
now? Shall I hide here?

1329
02:06:33,458 --> 02:06:38,334
He's come!

1330
02:06:45,208 --> 02:06:47,957
It seems that dad's mouth
has been gagged.

1331
02:06:47,958 --> 02:06:53,750
I must find another
way to go inside.

1332
02:07:12,041 --> 02:07:15,958
The killer has come. Please save me.

1333
02:07:16,083 --> 02:07:18,082
Please don't kill me. Don't kill me.

1334
02:07:18,083 --> 02:07:20,082
I'll die.
- Dad, it's me.

1335
02:07:20,083 --> 02:07:23,040
Don't kill me!
- Dad, it's me, Jojo.

1336
02:07:23,041 --> 02:07:25,416
It's you!
- Yes. Here's the latest news.

1337
02:07:25,417 --> 02:07:28,249
The car that we got frightened
of was our own car.

1338
02:07:28,250 --> 02:07:32,000
The mechanic had come to deliver
it. You, son of a donkey!

1339
02:07:33,208 --> 02:07:34,915
What was the need to break
the window pane...

1340
02:07:34,916 --> 02:07:36,915
...and come inside for that?

1341
02:07:36,916 --> 02:07:39,541
I banged against the door. But
you didn't open the door.

1342
02:07:39,542 --> 02:07:41,332
I thought that you'd
get a heart attack.

1343
02:07:41,333 --> 02:07:42,915
That's why I entered
through the window.

1344
02:07:42,916 --> 02:07:44,416
Your entry through the window...

1345
02:07:44,417 --> 02:07:46,499
...was itself a big heart
attack for me.

1346
02:07:46,500 --> 02:07:48,957
My heart was in my mouth.
If it had been big enough...

1347
02:07:48,958 --> 02:07:50,457
...then it would have come out.

1348
02:07:50,458 --> 02:07:54,541
This is the latest news.
- Shut up.

1349
02:07:54,542 --> 02:07:57,457
Now, I'll leave for Nagpur for
some days, tomorrow itself.

1350
02:07:57,458 --> 02:07:59,541
So that the killer doesn't
get to know about me.

1351
02:07:59,542 --> 02:08:01,457
Or else that killer will
kill me afterwards...

1352
02:08:01,458 --> 02:08:05,167
...but this worthless fellow
will kill me first. Donkey!

1353
02:08:05,458 --> 02:08:08,166
I'm tired of being called
as donkey and worthless.

1354
02:08:08,167 --> 02:08:10,416
Just see now. I'll prove it to you.

1355
02:08:10,417 --> 02:08:15,667
That I'm quite intelligent.

1356
02:08:27,208 --> 02:08:31,915
No, he's being just engaged...
- Raj, you've a call.

1357
02:08:31,916 --> 02:08:34,332
Hello, who is it?
- Your well-wisher.

1358
02:08:34,333 --> 02:08:39,333
Well-wisher? - Yes, I had
called you to give a tip.

1359
02:08:39,417 --> 02:08:42,833
Which tip? - The fourth partner
of the three people...

1360
02:08:42,916 --> 02:08:46,833
...that you've killed, Mr.
Anthony D'costa, is going...

1361
02:08:46,916 --> 02:08:49,915
...for a business meeting in Nagpur.

1362
02:08:49,916 --> 02:08:51,915
You've a really golden opportunity.

1363
02:08:51,916 --> 02:08:57,957
Finish him off between
Mumbai and Nagpur.

1364
02:08:57,958 --> 02:08:59,374
This is the latest news.

1365
02:08:59,375 --> 02:09:02,374
He takes the right message
and says it's wrong number.

1366
02:09:02,375 --> 02:09:05,500
Boss, what should we do now?
- My plan has become successful.

1367
02:09:05,958 --> 02:09:08,166
He got the tip.

1368
02:09:08,167 --> 02:09:11,874
In a few time from now he'll
set off to kill dad.

1369
02:09:11,875 --> 02:09:14,332
We'll follow him.

1370
02:09:14,333 --> 02:09:18,292
Before he finishes dad,
we'll finish him off!

1371
02:09:20,875 --> 02:09:22,332
I've escaped.

1372
02:09:22,333 --> 02:09:25,082
Man, I escaped from
my worthless son...

1373
02:09:25,083 --> 02:09:30,625
. and I've escaped from
that killer too.

1374
02:09:31,041 --> 02:09:32,915
You always considered
me as your worthless...

1375
02:09:32,916 --> 02:09:34,541
...and good for nothing son.

1376
02:09:34,542 --> 02:09:38,000
There's no need to consider that.
You were in fact born as worthless.

1377
02:09:38,083 --> 02:09:40,082
But from now on, your
misunderstanding...

1378
02:09:40,083 --> 02:09:42,040
...will be gone forever.

1379
02:09:42,041 --> 02:09:43,999
You are Raj's fourth target.

1380
02:09:44,000 --> 02:09:47,167
I'll prevent you from
being murdered.

1381
02:09:47,250 --> 02:09:49,541
But, that will only happen if
the killer comes to know of it.

1382
02:09:49,542 --> 02:09:53,333
Dad, I've told your killer Raj
that you're going to Nagpur.

1383
02:09:54,208 --> 02:09:57,207
What?

1384
02:09:57,208 --> 02:10:01,000
He'll try to attack you and
I'll catch him red-handed.

1385
02:10:01,125 --> 02:10:04,041
Hey, you donkey! Are you going
to get your father killed!

1386
02:10:04,042 --> 02:10:06,541
I have not told him
that you are my dad.

1387
02:10:06,542 --> 02:10:10,207
Well done! You are
really not my son.

1388
02:10:10,208 --> 02:10:13,833
This is the latest news.
- I'll give you the latest news.

1389
02:10:13,958 --> 02:10:17,375
If I escape alive, then you'll
not escape alive from me.

1390
02:10:18,000 --> 02:10:22,791
Oh God! What son have you given me!

1391
02:10:23,167 --> 02:10:26,166
Now, what shall I do?

1392
02:10:26,167 --> 02:10:29,791
If I go back to Mumbai, then
he'll kill me from the front.

1393
02:10:29,916 --> 02:10:32,082
If I go to Nagpur, then he'll
kill me from behind.

1394
02:10:32,083 --> 02:10:33,915
Now where shall I go?
Where shall I hide?

1395
02:10:33,916 --> 02:10:38,207
I'm confused about what I should do?

1396
02:10:38,208 --> 02:10:42,458
Hey, these are tribal hutments.

1397
02:10:42,459 --> 02:10:46,000
Tonight I'll have booze
and sleep here.

1398
02:10:46,208 --> 02:10:51,834
Let it happen, whatever happens?
I'll deal with it.

1399
02:10:55,916 --> 02:11:00,374
The hutment is shaking.

1400
02:11:00,375 --> 02:11:04,915
It started moving now.

1401
02:11:04,916 --> 02:11:11,000
Goodness me! Why is
this following me?

1402
02:11:13,875 --> 02:11:19,291
Let me run from here.

1403
02:11:20,000 --> 02:11:25,625
Hey! This hutment is following me.

1404
02:11:40,916 --> 02:11:44,334
My God! How did this hutment
get on my car?

1405
02:12:00,208 --> 02:12:05,834
You dare to get on my car!
Dare to get over me?

1406
02:12:08,958 --> 02:12:14,417
The... the killer's car!

1407
02:12:14,875 --> 02:12:17,874
There's no one in the car!
How's this possible!?

1408
02:12:17,875 --> 02:12:19,874
Who's driving the car, then?

1409
02:12:19,875 --> 02:12:26,291
Goodness me! How can I stop it?

1410
02:12:32,167 --> 02:12:33,874
No idea, who called.

1411
02:12:33,875 --> 02:12:39,458
Raj has come. Let's hide quickly.

1412
02:12:40,875 --> 02:12:43,124
Priya!
- Yes. My car is not to be seen.

1413
02:12:43,125 --> 02:12:46,167
What!? Where had you parked it?
- There, in front of the white car.

1414
02:12:46,334 --> 02:12:48,249
Oh God, Priya! If something
happens this time...

1415
02:12:48,250 --> 02:12:50,249
...then all the blame
will come on me.

1416
02:12:50,250 --> 02:12:52,416
I must go and write a complaint
in the police station.

1417
02:12:52,417 --> 02:12:54,416
Or else inspector Khurana will
not let me go free this time.

1418
02:12:54,417 --> 02:12:59,333
Then, let's go in my car.

1419
02:13:03,541 --> 02:13:09,500
Thank goodness! That the
car stopped following me.

1420
02:13:27,000 --> 02:13:30,041
I had told him to go towards
Nagpur and follow dad.

1421
02:13:30,042 --> 02:13:35,458
Why did he come to
the police station?

1422
02:13:42,167 --> 02:13:47,458
Good gracious! Its back!

1423
02:14:01,209 --> 02:14:06,667
The car stopped because of the kid.

1424
02:14:08,875 --> 02:14:12,167
Come. You want to kill
me, right? Come.

1425
02:14:12,958 --> 02:14:15,874
Run over my body. Come.

1426
02:14:15,875 --> 02:14:20,583
Kill me!

1427
02:14:32,000 --> 02:14:34,082
So, this is the funda.
- Yes, sir.

1428
02:14:34,083 --> 02:14:35,208
What do you think?

1429
02:14:35,209 --> 02:14:38,458
Who must have phoned you
to kill Anthony D'costa?

1430
02:14:38,541 --> 02:14:41,999
I don't know.

1431
02:14:42,000 --> 02:14:44,041
I'm Anthony D'costa here.

1432
02:14:44,042 --> 02:14:46,124
Yes, Mr. D'costa. Tell me.

1433
02:14:46,125 --> 02:14:50,167
Inspector, please save me.
Raj's car wants to kill me.

1434
02:14:50,292 --> 02:14:52,083
But, Raj is sitting
here in front of me.

1435
02:14:52,084 --> 02:14:55,041
How can this be possible? Check
properly, who is in the car?

1436
02:14:55,042 --> 02:14:56,333
He is my death.

1437
02:14:56,334 --> 02:14:59,208
I've no idea who is driving it
and how is it being driven!

1438
02:14:59,209 --> 02:15:00,540
From, where are you talking?

1439
02:15:00,541 --> 02:15:03,792
Inspector, that car is coming.
It's coming towards me.

1440
02:15:03,917 --> 02:15:06,333
Hello Mr. D'costa, tell
me. Where are you?

1441
02:15:06,334 --> 02:15:12,792
Inspector, please save
me. Please save me.

1442
02:15:16,209 --> 02:15:17,916
What happened, sir?

1443
02:15:17,917 --> 02:15:23,667
Someone killed Anthony D'costa.

1444
02:15:24,375 --> 02:15:25,540
Don't know who is that person...

1445
02:15:25,541 --> 02:15:27,916
...who drives the car time
and again and kills people.

1446
02:15:27,917 --> 02:15:29,916
And why does he want all
the blame to fall on me?

1447
02:15:29,917 --> 02:15:32,540
No idea, where's Tarzan right now?

1448
02:15:32,541 --> 02:15:34,916
I fear that a mishap
is going to happen.

1449
02:15:34,917 --> 02:15:37,499
Don't worry, Raj. When the
police have sealed...

1450
02:15:37,500 --> 02:15:40,208
...all the exits then Tarzan
certainly will be found.

1451
02:15:40,209 --> 02:15:43,957
And it may happen that the
person is caught, too.

1452
02:15:43,958 --> 02:15:48,875
Now, let me drop you home.

1453
02:16:10,917 --> 02:16:16,500
Can I talk to inspector Khurana?

1454
02:16:22,209 --> 02:16:27,000
So, when you came here, then this
car was already here? - Yes.

1455
02:16:28,042 --> 02:16:32,167
Does a computer drive this car?
- No.

1456
02:16:32,917 --> 02:16:37,333
Then does a robot drive this?
- Sir, what are you talking?

1457
02:16:37,416 --> 02:16:40,541
Then, what's the funda?
How did the car get here?

1458
02:16:41,959 --> 02:16:44,958
Mother, you were here previously.

1459
02:16:44,959 --> 02:16:48,000
Can you tell us something?
- No. I don't know.

1460
02:16:48,125 --> 02:16:50,208
You don't know.

1461
02:16:50,209 --> 02:16:51,958
While you were writing a complaint...

1462
02:16:51,959 --> 02:16:53,958
...that your car has been stolen,
right at that time...

1463
02:16:53,959 --> 02:16:55,958
...someone bumped Anthony D'costa...

1464
02:16:55,959 --> 02:16:59,000
...along with the telephone
booth, with your car.

1465
02:16:59,375 --> 02:17:01,958
And this car reached
its owner's house...

1466
02:17:01,959 --> 02:17:05,917
...just like a faithful dog.
What does this mean?

1467
02:17:06,042 --> 02:17:08,374
Sir, how can I tell you that?
I was with you at that time.

1468
02:17:08,375 --> 02:17:11,208
I'll tell you the real funda.
You give this car...

1469
02:17:11,209 --> 02:17:14,208
...to someone else and
make him do the murders

1470
02:17:14,209 --> 02:17:16,916
How can you say this? When you
don't have any evidence...

1471
02:17:16,917 --> 02:17:19,374
...against my grandson?

1472
02:17:19,375 --> 02:17:21,249
Will you believe it, if
someone tells you...

1473
02:17:21,250 --> 02:17:24,208
...that this car did
all the accidents?

1474
02:17:24,209 --> 02:17:28,042
I say that your jeep did
all the four murders.

1475
02:17:28,125 --> 02:17:31,374
What nonsense are you talking?
- I'm talking nonsense?

1476
02:17:31,375 --> 02:17:34,374
You say that this car bumped
off the telephone booth.

1477
02:17:34,375 --> 02:17:36,916
Do you see any scratches on it?

1478
02:17:36,917 --> 02:17:39,083
Well, even if a truck bumps
off a telephone booth...

1479
02:17:39,084 --> 02:17:40,999
...even it's bound to suffer damages.

1480
02:17:41,000 --> 02:17:43,041
You are a senior officer and...

1481
02:17:43,042 --> 02:17:45,124
...you don't have the brains
to understand this?

1482
02:17:45,125 --> 02:17:47,208
You've been talking fundas
since a long time.

1483
02:17:47,209 --> 02:17:49,540
My grandson himself phoned
and called you here.

1484
02:17:49,541 --> 02:17:52,290
And conversely, you are blaming him.

1485
02:17:52,291 --> 02:17:55,208
Now I'll take this car
to the commissioner...

1486
02:17:55,209 --> 02:17:57,374
...and ask him personally, whether
do you feel this car...

1487
02:17:57,375 --> 02:17:59,290
...has dashed a telephone booth?

1488
02:17:59,291 --> 02:18:01,166
You'll go to the commissioner?

1489
02:18:01,167 --> 02:18:04,207
If circumstances force me then
I'll even meet the home minister

1490
02:18:04,208 --> 02:18:07,583
Sir, it seems that our end is near.

1491
02:18:07,875 --> 02:18:09,874
Before this lady calls the
home minister to her home...

1492
02:18:09,875 --> 02:18:11,874
...and endangers our home...

1493
02:18:11,875 --> 02:18:17,791
...let's go to our home.

1494
02:18:22,208 --> 02:18:25,291
Mother, you better talk
about your influence...

1495
02:18:25,416 --> 02:18:28,499
...till the commissioner, home
minister and the top...

1496
02:18:28,500 --> 02:18:33,208
...to those officers whose earnings
depend upon the top.

1497
02:18:33,917 --> 02:18:37,916
Not with an officer like me.

1498
02:18:37,917 --> 02:18:42,333
And about this car. This car
is related to every murder.

1499
02:18:42,542 --> 02:18:44,916
I take this car in to
custody, right now.

1500
02:18:44,917 --> 02:18:46,499
Sitaram, bring the ropes.
- Yes, sir.

1501
02:18:46,500 --> 02:18:49,041
And tie this car to the jeep.

1502
02:18:49,042 --> 02:18:52,207
Please sir, don't take
this car away from me.

1503
02:18:52,208 --> 02:18:54,916
This is my father's last souvenir.

1504
02:18:54,917 --> 02:18:57,958
Sir, I promise you that
this car will never...

1505
02:18:57,959 --> 02:19:02,958
...create a mishap or an accident.

1506
02:19:02,959 --> 02:19:05,958
And what if it happens?
- Then I'm responsible for that.

1507
02:19:05,959 --> 02:19:08,874
You can arrest me.

1508
02:19:08,875 --> 02:19:14,291
Think again. This time I'll
not charge you with four...

1509
02:19:14,375 --> 02:19:17,959
...but five murders. That time I'll
not take this car in to custody.

1510
02:19:18,166 --> 02:19:20,207
I'll crush this car
like a matchbox...

1511
02:19:20,208 --> 02:19:22,207
...and throw it in some corner.

1512
02:19:22,208 --> 02:19:26,833
Did you get me?

1513
02:19:45,042 --> 02:19:47,249
What are you doing, son?

1514
02:19:47,250 --> 02:19:51,000
Granny, when I made Tarzan I
felt like papa is with me.

1515
02:19:51,917 --> 02:19:53,916
If Tarzan goes away from me...

1516
02:19:53,917 --> 02:19:59,375
...I'll feel that papa has gone too.

1517
02:20:43,917 --> 02:20:49,207
'My car.'

1518
02:20:49,208 --> 02:20:52,916
'My car.'

1519
02:20:52,917 --> 02:20:57,834
'Tarzan.'

1520
02:21:11,875 --> 02:21:13,040
What a pleasant surprise, papa?

1521
02:21:13,041 --> 02:21:14,165
But, you were supposed
to come tomorrow.

1522
02:21:14,166 --> 02:21:15,958
Why? Don't you like surprises?

1523
02:21:15,959 --> 02:21:17,541
Of course, I like them.

1524
02:21:17,542 --> 02:21:20,040
First tell me, how's Raj?
- He's very good, papa.

1525
02:21:20,041 --> 02:21:22,165
That's fantastic! Do one thing.

1526
02:21:22,166 --> 02:21:24,207
When you go to college
today, tell Raj...

1527
02:21:24,208 --> 02:21:29,040
...that I'll come to meet him
at his house in the evening.

1528
02:21:29,041 --> 02:21:32,458
And till that time, I'll meet
my old friends. Is that Ok?

1529
02:21:44,208 --> 02:21:46,916
How are you? And why is the
security all around here?

1530
02:21:46,917 --> 02:21:49,332
Kapoor uncle, you are still alive?

1531
02:21:49,333 --> 02:21:51,916
Hey, I'm absolutely fit and fine.

1532
02:21:51,917 --> 02:21:53,916
Tell me where's my friend Anthony.

1533
02:21:53,917 --> 02:21:55,999
Don't you know that dad went
along with Chopra uncle...

1534
02:21:56,000 --> 02:21:57,916
...Saxena uncle and inspector Sharma?

1535
02:21:57,917 --> 02:21:59,165
But, where did they go?

1536
02:21:59,166 --> 02:22:01,082
Did they go to some hill
station for picnic?

1537
02:22:01,083 --> 02:22:02,457
Then, tell me. I'll
go and meet them.

1538
02:22:02,458 --> 02:22:03,582
Well it's Priya's engagement...

1539
02:22:03,583 --> 02:22:05,916
...and I came to personally
invite them.

1540
02:22:05,917 --> 02:22:08,874
If you want to invite
them personally...

1541
02:22:08,875 --> 02:22:10,874
...then you've to go up.
- What?

1542
02:22:10,875 --> 02:22:15,583
Come. I'll tell you.

1543
02:22:16,875 --> 02:22:20,958
These... - These three have
been murdered. - What?

1544
02:22:21,041 --> 02:22:23,165
Dad was run over and
killed by a car.

1545
02:22:23,166 --> 02:22:24,374
And police said that the same car...

1546
02:22:24,375 --> 02:22:26,957
...had killed Chopra uncle
and Saxena uncle.

1547
02:22:26,958 --> 02:22:29,165
Has the murderer been found?

1548
02:22:29,166 --> 02:22:30,874
The police are still
searching for him.

1549
02:22:30,875 --> 02:22:33,958
And the car with which, they
were killed belongs...

1550
02:22:34,041 --> 02:22:40,292
...to an automobile engineer
Deven Chaudhary's son.

1551
02:22:42,000 --> 02:22:44,416
Yes. Police doubt that
that guy killed them...

1552
02:22:44,417 --> 02:22:46,916
...or made someone kill them.

1553
02:22:46,917 --> 02:22:49,999
Uncle, If he comes to
know that you've come...

1554
02:22:50,000 --> 02:22:52,916
...and you are their partner, then...

1555
02:22:52,917 --> 02:22:54,999
...you won't require to get a
London visa on your passport.

1556
02:22:55,000 --> 02:22:58,166
You'll die standing there and
your passport will get expired.

1557
02:23:03,916 --> 02:23:07,333
Uncle, what are you thinking?
- No... nothing.

1558
02:23:07,417 --> 02:23:09,874
I'll look in to this after
Priya's engagement.

1559
02:23:09,875 --> 02:23:13,625
You don't worry.

1560
02:23:14,041 --> 02:23:16,915
This is the latest news.
Why should I worry?

1561
02:23:16,916 --> 02:23:21,583
My dad's already dead.

1562
02:23:37,875 --> 02:23:41,874
Papa, this is Raj.

1563
02:23:41,875 --> 02:23:44,874
No, my son. A son-in-law
is just like a son.

1564
02:23:44,875 --> 02:23:48,915
And a son gives a hug. C'mon.

1565
02:23:48,916 --> 02:23:51,915
Granny, this is Priya's father.
And this is my granny.

1566
02:23:51,916 --> 02:23:53,082
Greetings!
- Greetings!

1567
02:23:53,083 --> 02:23:56,915
Please come in.
- Yes. - Have a seat.

1568
02:23:56,916 --> 02:23:59,915
I'm happy that you came here.

1569
02:23:59,916 --> 02:24:03,083
Priya always talks
about you on phone.

1570
02:24:03,208 --> 02:24:07,834
She tells that whenever I
meet granny I forget you.

1571
02:24:10,916 --> 02:24:13,207
...is going to become the
daughter-in-law of your house.

1572
02:24:13,208 --> 02:24:15,874
This is your greatness and...

1573
02:24:15,875 --> 02:24:17,874
...honestly speaking, this
is our good fortune.

1574
02:24:17,875 --> 02:24:20,040
Thank you.
- I'll bring tea for you.

1575
02:24:20,041 --> 02:24:24,917
Fine.

1576
02:24:35,875 --> 02:24:39,125
Uncle, that my father's photo.

1577
02:24:42,083 --> 02:24:47,792
Papa!?
- Yes.

1578
02:24:48,041 --> 02:24:50,874
Murderer of my father, now
do you know understand...

1579
02:24:50,875 --> 02:24:53,874
...why I pretended to
love your daughter.

1580
02:24:53,875 --> 02:24:55,915
To bring you here from London.

1581
02:24:55,916 --> 02:24:59,458
I've killed your other friends.

1582
02:24:59,916 --> 02:25:04,625
Now, it's your turn.

1583
02:25:06,916 --> 02:25:09,915
What happened, uncle?
- Nothing.

1584
02:25:09,916 --> 02:25:12,915
What happened, papa?
- Nothing, my child.

1585
02:25:12,916 --> 02:25:15,999
It seems like I'm not well.

1586
02:25:16,000 --> 02:25:18,082
Let's go from here.
- But papa... - Let's go.

1587
02:25:18,083 --> 02:25:19,332
How can you go this way?

1588
02:25:19,333 --> 02:25:20,458
You've come for the first
time in our house.

1589
02:25:20,459 --> 02:25:21,915
At least have some tea.
- No. It's all right.

1590
02:25:21,916 --> 02:25:23,583
But, uncle...
- We'll talk later son.

1591
02:25:23,584 --> 02:25:25,915
Come, Priya.
- But papa, what happened?

1592
02:25:25,916 --> 02:25:28,915
We had come just now.

1593
02:25:28,916 --> 02:25:31,040
What happened to him so suddenly?

1594
02:25:31,041 --> 02:25:33,915
He was telling that he was not well.

1595
02:25:33,916 --> 02:25:35,957
He was not feeling well?

1596
02:25:35,958 --> 02:25:37,957
Papa, you were all right.

1597
02:25:37,958 --> 02:25:39,207
Then why did we come from there?

1598
02:25:39,208 --> 02:25:42,500
Because I don't want
you to marry him.

1599
02:25:42,958 --> 02:25:45,040
What happened to you so suddenly?

1600
02:25:45,041 --> 02:25:46,207
Why are you saying like this?

1601
02:25:46,208 --> 02:25:48,957
No arguments. I don't
want to hear anything.

1602
02:25:48,958 --> 02:25:51,124
We'll both go back to London.

1603
02:25:51,125 --> 02:25:53,458
And you'll marry a boy of my choice.

1604
02:25:53,459 --> 02:25:55,541
And this is my final decision.
Understood?

1605
02:25:55,542 --> 02:25:57,957
Then, listen to my decision too.

1606
02:25:57,958 --> 02:25:59,957
I'll marry no one, but Raj.

1607
02:25:59,958 --> 02:26:05,667
If you want to go to London,
then you can go alone.

1608
02:26:15,208 --> 02:26:17,915
Raj, my son. A calamity has struck!

1609
02:26:17,916 --> 02:26:22,333
That scum Rakesh Kapoor is taking
your Priya to London.

1610
02:26:22,417 --> 02:26:25,500
He wants her to marry someone else.

1611
02:26:25,916 --> 02:26:27,999
What?!
- Please save Priya.

1612
02:26:28,000 --> 02:26:30,915
Dear Priya is immersed in tears.

1613
02:26:30,916 --> 02:26:34,000
If it was under my control
then I would have cut...

1614
02:26:34,083 --> 02:26:37,041
...that scum Kapoor's
rear with an axe.

1615
02:26:37,042 --> 02:26:43,875
But, what can I do, son? I can't
lift in this old age... the axe.

1616
02:26:43,958 --> 02:26:47,584
But, who are you?
- I'm Kapoor's gardener.

1617
02:26:47,958 --> 02:26:51,041
Son, you are coming, right?
- Yes, I'm coming.

1618
02:26:51,042 --> 02:26:53,207
Latest news. Uncle, he's coming.

1619
02:26:53,208 --> 02:26:54,374
You uncultured brute!

1620
02:26:54,375 --> 02:26:56,207
You were heaving curses
on me, in my presence.

1621
02:26:56,208 --> 02:26:58,957
Uncle, if I had not
cursed you, then...

1622
02:26:58,958 --> 02:27:00,957
...how would have he believed
that I was in his favor?

1623
02:27:00,958 --> 02:27:03,541
You don't know. To catch a lion
you have to cut a pig...

1624
02:27:03,542 --> 02:27:07,874
...and throw it as a
bait in front of him.

1625
02:27:07,875 --> 02:27:10,915
Where are you going, son?
- I got a call from Priya's house.

1626
02:27:10,916 --> 02:27:14,082
Her father is taking her
to London forever.

1627
02:27:14,083 --> 02:27:16,333
How can he take her in this way?

1628
02:27:16,334 --> 02:27:18,915
Priya and I love each
other very much.

1629
02:27:18,916 --> 02:27:20,999
Granny, I can't live without her.

1630
02:27:21,000 --> 02:27:23,207
I won't allow her to go.
- Wait, son.

1631
02:27:23,208 --> 02:27:27,417
I'll come with you too. How can
he hurt children's hearts?

1632
02:27:27,542 --> 02:27:32,500
I'll talk to him. Come.

1633
02:28:13,875 --> 02:28:16,915
Raj, are you going to meet Priya?

1634
02:28:16,916 --> 02:28:19,041
But you'll never be able
to meet anyone again.

1635
02:28:19,042 --> 02:28:22,125
Because it was me who deceived
you to come here.

1636
02:28:23,208 --> 02:28:26,207
I'll kill you and throw you here.

1637
02:28:26,208 --> 02:28:32,625
I challenge you. Come out.

1638
02:28:40,917 --> 02:28:42,999
Granny, that is Tarzan.

1639
02:28:43,000 --> 02:28:48,834
But, how did it reach here?

1640
02:28:53,125 --> 02:28:54,291
Sir, your planning was very good!

1641
02:28:54,292 --> 02:28:56,374
You threw that Raj along
with his car...

1642
02:28:56,375 --> 02:28:58,124
...from the mountain and killed him.

1643
02:28:58,125 --> 02:29:01,167
People will think that this is
an accident, but not murder.

1644
02:29:02,208 --> 02:29:04,957
No!
- Priya!

1645
02:29:04,958 --> 02:29:06,957
Priya, stop.

1646
02:29:06,958 --> 02:29:11,292
Granny, my Tarzan! How
did this happen?

1647
02:29:11,875 --> 02:29:17,291
Who did this, granny?

1648
02:29:17,875 --> 02:29:20,957
I was shocked when
I heard that papa...

1649
02:29:20,958 --> 02:29:22,916
...threw you along with Tarzan
from the mountain.

1650
02:29:22,917 --> 02:29:26,916
That means, your papa did all this.

1651
02:29:26,917 --> 02:29:29,249
Yes, I've done it.

1652
02:29:29,250 --> 02:29:31,082
And look, what I do next.

1653
02:29:31,083 --> 02:29:33,916
Papa, please stop.
- Move aside.

1654
02:29:33,917 --> 02:29:35,916
Uncle, please leave her.

1655
02:29:35,917 --> 02:29:38,916
Take her away.

1656
02:29:38,917 --> 02:29:41,916
What are you doing? Leave him.

1657
02:29:41,917 --> 02:29:43,416
Move aside. Move from here.

1658
02:29:43,417 --> 02:29:48,709
I won't leave you. Come.

1659
02:29:57,209 --> 02:29:59,333
Uncle, what are you doing?

1660
02:29:59,334 --> 02:30:01,208
First, you killed my accomplices.

1661
02:30:01,209 --> 02:30:04,208
Now, you want to kill me?

1662
02:30:04,209 --> 02:30:07,874
Uncle, I didn't kill anyone.

1663
02:30:07,875 --> 02:30:10,957
I'll kill you in the same way like...

1664
02:30:10,958 --> 02:30:16,959
...I drowned and killed your father

1665
02:32:56,209 --> 02:32:58,208
This car! This had been
shattered to pieces.

1666
02:32:58,209 --> 02:33:02,833
How did this get here?

1667
02:35:04,208 --> 02:35:08,791
Granny.

1668
02:35:24,917 --> 02:35:27,249
No, Devan. Please forgive me.

1669
02:35:27,250 --> 02:35:31,000
Have mercy on me.
- Did you have mercy on me?

1670
02:35:32,917 --> 02:35:35,041
Did you ever realize,
what would happen...

1671
02:35:35,042 --> 02:35:37,958
...to my mother and my
son after I'm gone?

1672
02:35:37,959 --> 02:35:40,041
My soul was writhing
for twelve years...

1673
02:35:40,042 --> 02:35:42,958
...seeing you and your
accomplices alive.

1674
02:35:42,959 --> 02:35:45,958
Perhaps, it was my mother's
blessings...

1675
02:35:45,959 --> 02:35:49,375
...that my son brought
my car before you.

1676
02:35:50,000 --> 02:35:53,250
If I wanted then I could have
killed you there itself...

1677
02:35:53,375 --> 02:35:56,958
...where you were drowning my son.

1678
02:35:56,959 --> 02:35:59,958
But, I wanted to prove that
my son was innocent.

1679
02:35:59,959 --> 02:36:01,541
That's why I brought you here.

1680
02:36:01,542 --> 02:36:04,124
I accept in front of everyone
that I'm your culprit.

1681
02:36:04,125 --> 02:36:06,999
My accomplices and I had
stolen your car's design.

1682
02:36:07,000 --> 02:36:09,207
And killed you by deceit.

1683
02:36:09,208 --> 02:36:13,000
Inspector, please arrest me.

1684
02:36:14,208 --> 02:36:18,416
Mr. Kapoor, this is called
the nature's funda.

1685
02:36:19,917 --> 02:36:22,916
Humans commit sins and
try to conceal them.

1686
02:36:22,917 --> 02:36:27,000
But nature unfolds it
and reveals them.

1687
02:36:35,917 --> 02:36:37,207
Mother!

1688
02:36:37,208 --> 02:36:39,249
Son, I was sure that an ill-omened...

1689
02:36:39,250 --> 02:36:42,124
...thing had happened to you.

1690
02:36:42,125 --> 02:36:44,207
Otherwise there's no
place in this world...

1691
02:36:44,208 --> 02:36:47,333
...where a son goes and
forgets his mother.

1692
02:36:48,042 --> 02:36:51,124
When a mother dies in
front of her child...

1693
02:36:51,125 --> 02:36:54,958
...then that mother lives forever.

1694
02:36:54,959 --> 02:36:57,958
When a child dies in
front of his mother...

1695
02:36:57,959 --> 02:37:01,207
...then that mother dies
a thousand deaths.

1696
02:37:01,208 --> 02:37:04,333
Isn't that son unfortunate
who had to leave...

1697
02:37:04,458 --> 02:37:08,458
...his mother and son
crying and perplexed?

1698
02:37:09,917 --> 02:37:13,458
See, even after my death
these eyes are open.

1699
02:37:14,917 --> 02:37:19,333
At the time of my death it
wanted to see you and Raj.

1700
02:37:19,917 --> 02:37:23,333
But neither could it see you...

1701
02:37:23,417 --> 02:37:28,166
...nor did your hands
close the eyelids.

1702
02:37:29,917 --> 02:37:32,916
Mother, if there is a rebirth...

1703
02:37:32,917 --> 02:37:36,166
...then I'll be born
again as your son.

1704
02:37:39,917 --> 02:37:43,834
Papa, you'll leave us and go away?

1705
02:37:47,917 --> 02:37:51,040
I had gone away twelve years back.

1706
02:37:51,041 --> 02:37:52,457
But, it was you...

1707
02:37:52,458 --> 02:37:56,958
...who brought me again
to my mother and you.

1708
02:37:56,959 --> 02:38:01,958
I'm sad that your father couldn't
do anything for you.

1709
02:38:01,959 --> 02:38:04,040
But, I'm happy...

1710
02:38:04,041 --> 02:38:07,207
...that you made a
better car than me.

1711
02:38:07,208 --> 02:38:11,792
And yes, the next time you
take Priya on a ride...

1712
02:38:11,875 --> 02:38:15,166
...don't take your hands
of the steering wheel.

1713
02:38:20,917 --> 02:38:26,625
I'll take your leave.

1714
02:38:44,917 --> 02:38:49,875
'You are the feeling...

1715
02:38:50,041 --> 02:38:55,834
...attached to my heart.'

